class RepositoryObserver < ActiveRecord::Observer


  		





  
  2
  
    

  		





  
  3
  
    
    def before_destroy(repository)


  		





  
  4
  
    
        if repository.created_with_scm


  		





  
  5
  
    
            project = repository.project


  		





  
  6
  
    

  		





  
  7
  
    
            type = repository.type


  		





  
  8
  
    
            type.gsub!(%r{^Repository::}, '')


  		





  
  9
  
    

  		





  
  10
  
    
            begin


  		





  
  11
  
    
                interface = Object.const_get("#{type}Creator")


  		





  
  12
  
    

  		





  
  13
  
    
                name = interface.repository_name(repository.root_url)


  		





  
  14
  
    
                if name


  		





  
  15
  
    
                    path = interface.path(name)


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
                    interface.execute(ScmConfig['pre_delete'], path, project) if ScmConfig['pre_delete']


  		





  
  18
  
    

  		





  
  19
  
    
                    FileUtils.remove_entry_secure(path, true)


  		





  
  20
  
    

  		





  
  21
  
    
                    interface.execute(ScmConfig['post_delete'], path, project) if ScmConfig['post_delete']


  		





  
  22
  
    

  		





  
  23
  
    
                end


  		





  
  24
  
    
            rescue NameError


  		





  
  25
  
    
            end


  		





  
  26
  
    

  		





  
  27
  
    
        end


  		





  
  28
  
    
    end


  		





  
  29
  
    

  		





  
  30
  
    
end

class SCMCreator


  		





  
  2
  
    

  		





  
  3
  
    
    class << self


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
        # returns config id used in scm.yml and ScmConfig


  		





  
  6
  
    
        def scm_id


  		





  
  7
  
    
            if self.name =~ %r{^(.+)Creator$}


  		





  
  8
  
    
                $1.downcase


  		





  
  9
  
    
            else


  		





  
  10
  
    
                nil


  		





  
  11
  
    
            end


  		





  
  12
  
    
        end


  		





  
  13
  
    

  		





  
  14
  
    
        # returns true if SCM is enabled


  		





  
  15
  
    
        def enabled?


  		





  
  16
  
    
            false


  		





  
  17
  
    
        end


  		





  
  18
  
    

  		





  
  19
  
    
        # returns configuration from scm.yml


  		





  
  20
  
    
        def options


  		





  
  21
  
    
            @options ||= ScmConfig[scm_id]


  		





  
  22
  
    
        end


  		





  
  23
  
    

  		





  
  24
  
    
        # returns local path used to access repository locally (with optional /.git/ etc)


  		





  
  25
  
    
        def access_url(path)


  		





  
  26
  
    
            if options['append']


  		





  
  27
  
    
                if Redmine::Platform.mswin?


  		





  
  28
  
    
                    "#{access_root_url(path)}\\#{options['append']}"


  		





  
  29
  
    
                else


  		





  
  30
  
    
                    "#{access_root_url(path)}/#{options['append']}"


  		





  
  31
  
    
                end


  		





  
  32
  
    
            else


  		





  
  33
  
    
                access_root_url(path)


  		





  
  34
  
    
            end


  		





  
  35
  
    
        end


  		





  
  36
  
    

  		





  
  37
  
    
        # returns local path used to access repository locally


  		





  
  38
  
    
        def access_root_url(path)


  		





  
  39
  
    
            path


  		





  
  40
  
    
        end


  		





  
  41
  
    

  		





  
  42
  
    
        # returns local path


  		





  
  43
  
    
        def path(identifier)


  		





  
  44
  
    
            if Redmine::Platform.mswin?


  		





  
  45
  
    
                # Assuming path is in Windows style (contains \'s)


  		





  
  46
  
    
                "#{options['path']}\\#{identifier}"


  		





  
  47
  
    
            else


  		





  
  48
  
    
                "#{options['path']}/#{identifier}"


  		





  
  49
  
    
            end


  		





  
  50
  
    
        end


  		





  
  51
  
    

  		





  
  52
  
    
        # returns url which can used to access the repository externally


  		





  
  53
  
    
        def external_url(name, regexp = %r{^https?://})


  		





  
  54
  
    
            if options['url'] =~ regexp


  		





  
  55
  
    
                url = "#{options['url']}/#{name}"


  		





  
  56
  
    
            else


  		





  
  57
  
    
                url = "#{Setting.protocol}://#{Setting.host_name}/#{options['url']}/#{name}"


  		





  
  58
  
    
            end


  		





  
  59
  
    
        end


  		





  
  60
  
    

  		





  
  61
  
    
        # constructs default path using project identifier


  		





  
  62
  
    
        def default_path(identifier)


  		





  
  63
  
    
            path(identifier)


  		





  
  64
  
    
        end


  		





  
  65
  
    

  		





  
  66
  
    
        # extracts repository name from path


  		





  
  67
  
    
        def repository_name(path)


  		





  
  68
  
    
            base = Redmine::Platform.mswin? ? options['path'].gsub!(%r{\\}, "/") : options['path']


  		





  
  69
  
    
            matches = Regexp.new("^#{Regexp.escape(base)}/([^/]+)/?$").match(path)


  		





  
  70
  
    
            matches ? matches[1] : nil


  		





  
  71
  
    
        end


  		





  
  72
  
    

  		





  
  73
  
    
        # compares repository names (was created for Git which can add .git extension)


  		





  
  74
  
    
        def repository_name_equal?(name, identifier)


  		





  
  75
  
    
            name == identifier


  		





  
  76
  
    
        end


  		





  
  77
  
    

  		





  
  78
  
    
        # returns format of repository path which is displayed in the form as a default value


  		





  
  79
  
    
        def repository_format


  		





  
  80
  
    
            path = Redmine::Platform.mswin? ? options['path'].gsub!(%r{\\}, "/") : options['path']


  		





  
  81
  
    
            "#{path}/<#{l(:label_repository_format)}>/"


  		





  
  82
  
    
        end


  		





  
  83
  
    

  		





  
  84
  
    
        # checks if repository already exists (was created for Git which can add .git extension)


  		





  
  85
  
    
        def repository_exists?(identifier)


  		





  
  86
  
    
            File.directory?(default_path(identifier))


  		





  
  87
  
    
        end


  		





  
  88
  
    

  		





  
  89
  
    
        # creates repository


  		





  
  90
  
    
        def create_repository(path)


  		





  
  91
  
    
            false


  		





  
  92
  
    
        end


  		





  
  93
  
    

  		





  
  94
  
    
        # copies hooks (obsolete)


  		





  
  95
  
    
        def copy_hooks(path)


  		





  
  96
  
    
            if options['hooks']


  		





  
  97
  
    
                RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.warn "Option 'hooks' is obsolete - use 'post_create' instead. See: http://projects.andriylesyuk.com/issues/1886."


  		





  
  98
  
    
                if File.directory?(options['hooks'])


  		





  
  99
  
    
                    args = [ '/bin/cp', '-aR' ]


  		





  
  100
  
    
                    args += Dir.glob("#{options['hooks']}/*")


  		





  
  101
  
    
                    args << "#{path}/hooks/"


  		





  
  102
  
    
                    system(*args)


  		





  
  103
  
    
                else


  		





  
  104
  
    
                    RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.error "Hooks directory #{options['hooks']} does not exist."


  		





  
  105
  
    
                    false


  		





  
  106
  
    
                end


  		





  
  107
  
    
            else


  		





  
  108
  
    
                true


  		





  
  109
  
    
            end


  		





  
  110
  
    
        end


  		





  
  111
  
    

  		





  
  112
  
    
        # executes custom scripts


  		





  
  113
  
    
        def execute(script, path, project)


  		





  
  114
  
    
            if File.executable?(script)


  		





  
  115
  
    
                project.custom_field_values.each do |custom_value|


  		





  
  116
  
    
                    name = custom_value.custom_field.name.gsub(%r{[^a-z0-9]+}i, '_').upcase


  		





  
  117
  
    
                    ENV["SCM_CUSTOM_FIELD_#{name}"] = custom_value.value unless name.empty?


  		





  
  118
  
    
                end


  		





  
  119
  
    
                system(script, path, scm_id, project.identifier)


  		





  
  120
  
    
            else


  		





  
  121
  
    
                RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.warn "cannot find/execute: #{script}"


  		





  
  122
  
    
            end


  		





  
  123
  
    
        end


  		





  
  124
  
    

  		





  
  125
  
    
        # initializes required properties of repository (used for Bazaar which requires log_encoding)


  		





  
  126
  
    
        def init_repository(repository)


  		





  
  127
  
    
        end

        def repository_name(path)


  		





  
  46
  
    
            base = Redmine::Platform.mswin? ? options['path'].gsub!(%r{\\}, "/") : options['path']


  		





  
  47
  
    
            matches = Regexp.new("^file://#{Regexp.escape(base)}/([^/]+)/?$").match(path)


  		





  
  48
  
    
            matches ? matches[1] : nil

        end

class ScmHook  < Redmine::Hook::ViewListener

    def view_projects_form(context = {})


  		





  
  4
  
    
        if context[:project].new_record? && ScmConfig['auto_create']


  		





  
  5
  
    
            count = [ SubversionCreator, GitCreator, MercurialCreator, BazaarCreator ].inject(0) do |sum, scm|


  		





  
  6
  
    
                sum += 1 if scm.enabled?


  		





  
  7
  
    
                sum


  		





  
  8
  
    
            end


  		





  
  9
  
    
            if (count > 1) || (ScmConfig['auto_create'] != 'force')


  		





  
  10
  
    
                row = ''


  		





  
  11
  
    
                row << label_tag('project[scm]', l(:field_scm) + (ScmConfig['auto_create'] == 'force' ? ' ' + content_tag(:span, '*', :class => 'required') : ''))


  		





  
  12
  
    
                row << select_tag('project[scm]', project_scm_options_for_select(context[:request].params[:project] ? context[:request].params[:project][:scm] : nil))


  		





  
  13
  
    
                row << '<br />' + content_tag(:em, l(:text_cannot_be_changed_later)) if ScmConfig['auto_create'] == 'force'


  		





  
  14
  
    
                content_tag(:p, row)


  		





  
  15
  
    
            else


  		





  
  16
  
    
                if SubversionCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  17
  
    
                    hidden_field_tag('project[scm]', 'Subversion')


  		





  
  18
  
    
                elsif GitCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  19
  
    
                    hidden_field_tag('project[scm]', 'Git')


  		





  
  20
  
    
                elsif MercurialCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  21
  
    
                    hidden_field_tag('project[scm]', 'Mercurial')


  		





  
  22
  
    
                elsif BazaarCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  23
  
    
                    hidden_field_tag('project[scm]', 'Bazaar')


  		





  
  24
  
    
                end


  		





  
  25
  
    
            end


  		





  
  26
  
    
        end


  		





  
  27
  
    
    end

    def controller_project_aliases_rename_after(context = {})


  		





  
  30
  
    
        if context[:project].repository && context[:project].repository.created_with_scm


  		





  
  31
  
    

  		





  
  32
  
    
            type = context[:project].repository.type


  		





  
  33
  
    
            type.gsub!(%r{^Repository::}, '')


  		





  
  34
  
    

  		





  
  35
  
    
            begin


  		





  
  36
  
    
                interface = Object.const_get("#{type}Creator")


  		





  
  37
  
    

  		





  
  38
  
    
                name = interface.repository_name(context[:project].repository.root_url)


  		





  
  39
  
    
                if name && interface.repository_name_equal?(name, context[:old_identifier])


  		





  
  40
  
    
                    old_path = interface.path(name)


  		





  
  41
  
    
                    if File.directory?(old_path)


  		





  
  42
  
    
                        new_path = interface.default_path(context[:new_identifier])


  		





  
  43
  
    
                        File.rename(old_path, new_path)


  		





  
  44
  
    

  		





  
  45
  
    
                        url = interface.access_url(new_path)


  		





  
  46
  
    
                        root_url = interface.access_root_url(new_path)


  		





  
  47
  
    
                        context[:project].repository.update_attributes(:root_url => root_url, :url => url)


  		





  
  48
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  49
  
    
                end


  		





  
  50
  
    
            rescue NameError


  		





  
  51
  
    
            end


  		





  
  52
  
    
        end


  		





  
  53
  
    
    end

    def project_scm_options_for_select(selected = nil)


  		





  
  58
  
    
        options = []


  		





  
  59
  
    
        options << [ '' ]           if ScmConfig['auto_create'] != 'force'


  		





  
  60
  
    
        options << [ 'Subversion' ] if SubversionCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  61
  
    
        options << [ 'Mercurial' ]  if MercurialCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  62
  
    
        options << [ 'Bazaar' ]     if BazaarCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  63
  
    
        options << [ 'Git' ]        if GitCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  64
  
    
        options_for_select(options, selected)


  		





  
  65
  
    
    end

    def self.included(base)

            safe_attributes 'scm' unless Redmine::VERSION::MAJOR == 1 && Redmine::VERSION::MINOR == 0 # Redmine 1.0.x

        def create_scm


  		





  
  35
  
    
            if @scm.present? && ScmConfig['auto_create']


  		





  
  36
  
    
                @repository = Repository.factory(@scm)


  		





  
  37
  
    
                if @repository


  		





  
  38
  
    
                    @repository.project = self


  		





  
  39
  
    

  		





  
  40
  
    
                    begin


  		





  
  41
  
    
                        interface = Object.const_get("#{@scm}Creator")


  		





  
  42
  
    
                        path = interface.default_path(self.identifier)


  		





  
  43
  
    

  		





  
  44
  
    
                        if File.directory?(path)


  		





  
  45
  
    
                            RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.warn "Automatically using reporitory: #{path}"


  		





  
  46
  
    
                        else


  		





  
  47
  
    
                            RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.info "Automatically creating reporitory: #{path}"


  		





  
  48
  
    
                            interface.execute(ScmConfig['pre_create'], path, self) if ScmConfig['pre_create']


  		





  
  49
  
    
                            if interface.create_repository(path)


  		





  
  50
  
    
                                interface.execute(ScmConfig['post_create'], path, self) if ScmConfig['post_create']


  		





  
  51
  
    
                                @repository.created_with_scm = true


  		





  
  52
  
    
                                unless interface.copy_hooks(path)


  		





  
  53
  
    
                                    RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.warn "Hooks copy failed"


  		





  
  54
  
    
                                end


  		





  
  55
  
    
                            else


  		





  
  56
  
    
                                RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.error "Repository creation failed"


  		





  
  57
  
    
                            end


  		





  
  58
  
    
                        end


  		





  
  59
  
    

  		





  
  60
  
    
                        interface.init_repository(@repository) if @repository.new_record?


  		





  
  61
  
    
                        @repository.root_url = interface.access_root_url(path)


  		





  
  62
  
    
                        @repository.url = interface.access_url(path)


  		





  
  63
  
    
                        @repository.save


  		





  
  64
  
    

  		





  
  65
  
    
                    rescue NameError


  		





  
  66
  
    
                        RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.error "Can't find interface for #{@scm}."


  		





  
  67
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  68
  
    
                end


  		





  
  69
  
    
            end


  		





  
  70
  
    
        end


  		





  
  71
  
    

  		





  
  72
  
    
        def repository_exists


  		





  
  73
  
    
            if @scm.present? && self.identifier.present? && ScmConfig['auto_create']


  		





  
  74
  
    
                begin


  		





  
  75
  
    
                    interface = Object.const_get("#{@scm}Creator")


  		





  
  76
  
    
                    if interface.repository_exists?(self.identifier)


  		





  
  77
  
    
                        errors.add_to_base(:repository_exists_for_identifier)


  		





  
  78
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  79

  80
  
    
                    RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.error "Can't find interface for #{@scm}."

        def edit_with_add


  		





  
  59

                    else


  		





  
  73
  
    
                        attrs[name] = value


  		





  
  74
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  75
  
    
                end


  		





  
  76
  
    
                @repository.attributes = attrs


  		





  
  77
  
    

  		





  
  78
  
    
                if @repository.valid? && params[:operation].present? && params[:operation] == 'add'


  		





  
  79
  
    
                    if attrs


  		





  
  80
  
    

  		





  
  81
  
    
                        begin


  		





  
  82
  
    
                            interface = Object.const_get("#{params[:repository_scm]}Creator")


  		





  
  83
  
    

  		





  
  84
  
    
                            name = interface.repository_name(attrs['url'])


  		





  
  85
  
    
                            if name


  		





  
  86
  
    
                                path = interface.path(name)


  		





  
  87
  
    
                                if File.directory?(path)


  		





  
  88
  
    
                                    @repository.errors.add(:url, :already_exists)


  		





  
  89
  
    
                                else


  		





  
  90
  
    
                                    RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.info "Creating reporitory: #{path}"


  		





  
  91
  
    
                                    interface.execute(ScmConfig['pre_create'], path, @project) if ScmConfig['pre_create']


  		





  
  92
  
    
                                    if interface.create_repository(path)


  		





  
  93
  
    
                                        interface.execute(ScmConfig['post_create'], path, @project) if ScmConfig['post_create']


  		





  
  94
  
    
                                        @repository.created_with_scm = true


  		





  
  95
  
    
                                        unless interface.copy_hooks(path)


  		





  
  96
  
    
                                            RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.warn "Hooks copy failed"


  		





  
  97
  
    
                                        end


  		





  
  98
  
    
                                    else


  		





  
  99
  
    
                                        RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.error "Repository creation failed"


  		





  
  100
  
    
                                    end


  		





  
  101
  
    
                                end


  		





  
  102
  
    

  		





  
  103
  
    
                                @repository.root_url = interface.access_root_url(path)


  		





  
  104
  
    
                                @repository.url = interface.access_url(path)


  		





  
  105
  
    

  		





  
  106
  
    
                                if !interface.repository_name_equal?(name, @project.identifier)


  		





  
  107
  
    
                                    flash[:warning] = l(:text_cannot_be_used_redmine_auth)


  		





  
  108
  
    
                                end


  		





  
  109
  
    
                            else


  		





  
  110
  
    
                                @repository.errors.add(:url, :should_be_of_format_local, :format => interface.repository_format)


  		





  
  111
  
    
                            end


  		





  
  112
  
    

  		





  
  113
  
    
                        rescue NameError


  		





  
  114
  
    
                            RAILS_DEFAULT_LOGGER.error "Can't find interface for #{params[:repository_scm]}."


  		





  
  115
  
    
                            @repository.errors.add_to_base(:scm_not_supported)


  		





  
  116
  
    
                        end


  		





  
  117
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  118
  
    
                end


  		





  
  119
  
    

  		





  
  120
  
    
                if @repository.errors.empty?


  		





  
  121
  
    
                    @repository.merge_extra_info(extra) if @repository.respond_to?(:merge_extra_info)


  		





  
  122
  
    
                    @repository.save


  		





  
  123
  
    
                end


  		





  
  124
  
    
            end


  		





  
  125
  
    

  		





  
  126
  
    
            render(:update) do |page|


  		





  
  127
  
    
                page.replace_html("tab-content-repository", :partial => 'projects/settings/repository')


  		





  
  128
  
    
                if @repository && !@project.repository


  		





  
  129
  
    
                    @project.reload


  		





  
  130
  
    
                    page.replace_html("main-menu", render_main_menu(@project))


  		





  
  131
  
    
                end


  		





  
  132
  
    
            end


  		





  
  133
  
    
        end


  		





  
  134
  
    

  		





  
  135
  
    
    end


  		





  
  136
  
    

  		





  
  137
  
    
end


  		












  

    
      b/vendor/plugins.inactive/redmine_scm/lib/scm_repositories_helper_patch.rb
    
  






  
  1
  
    
require_dependency 'repositories_helper'


  		





  
  2
  
    

  		





  
  3
  
    
module ScmRepositoriesHelperPatch


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
    def self.included(base)


  		





  
  6
  
    
        base.extend(ClassMethods)


  		





  
  7
  
    
        base.send(:include, InstanceMethods)


  		





  
  8
  
    
        base.class_eval do


  		





  
  9
  
    
            unloadable


  		





  
  10
  
    
            alias_method_chain :subversion_field_tags, :add


  		





  
  11
  
    
            alias_method_chain :mercurial_field_tags,  :add


  		





  
  12
  
    
            alias_method_chain :git_field_tags,        :add


  		





  
  13
  
    
            alias_method_chain :bazaar_field_tags,     :add


  		





  
  14
  
    
        end


  		





  
  15
  
    
    end


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
    module ClassMethods


  		





  
  18
  
    
    end


  		





  
  19
  
    

  		





  
  20
  
    
    module InstanceMethods


  		





  
  21
  
    

  		





  
  22
  
    
        def subversion_field_tags_with_add(form, repository)


  		





  
  23
  
    
            svntags = subversion_field_tags_without_add(form, repository)


  		





  
  24
  
    

  		





  
  25
  
    
            if !@project.repository && SubversionCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  26
  
    
                add = submit_tag(l(:button_create_new_repository), :onclick => "$('repository_operation').value = 'add';")


  		





  
  27
  
    
                svntags['<br />'] = ' ' + add + '<br />'


  		





  
  28
  
    
                svntags << hidden_field_tag(:operation, '', :id => 'repository_operation')


  		





  
  29
  
    
                unless request.post?


  		





  
  30
  
    
                    path = SubversionCreator.access_root_url(SubversionCreator.default_path(@project.identifier))


  		





  
  31
  
    
                    svntags << javascript_tag("$('repository_url').value = '#{escape_javascript(path)}';")


  		





  
  32
  
    
                end


  		





  
  33
  
    

  		





  
  34
  
    
            elsif @project.repository && @project.repository.created_with_scm &&


  		





  
  35
  
    
                SubversionCreator.enabled? && SubversionCreator.options['url'].present?


  		





  
  36
  
    
                name = SubversionCreator.repository_name(@project.repository.root_url)


  		





  
  37
  
    
                if name


  		





  
  38
  
    
                    svntags['(file:///, http://, https://, svn://, svn+[tunnelscheme]://)'] = SubversionCreator.external_url(name)


  		





  
  39
  
    
                end


  		





  
  40
  
    
            end


  		





  
  41
  
    

  		





  
  42
  
    
            return svntags


  		





  
  43
  
    
        end


  		





  
  44
  
    

  		





  
  45
  
    
        def mercurial_field_tags_with_add(form, repository)


  		





  
  46
  
    
            hgtags = mercurial_field_tags_without_add(form, repository)


  		





  
  47
  
    

  		





  
  48
  
    
            if !@project.repository && MercurialCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  49
  
    
                add = submit_tag(l(:button_create_new_repository), :onclick => "$('repository_operation').value = 'add';")


  		





  
  50
  
    
                if hgtags.include?('<br />')


  		





  
  51
  
    
                    hgtags['<br />'] = ' ' + add + '<br />'


  		





  
  52
  
    
                else


  		





  
  53
  
    
                    hgtags['</p>'] = ' ' + add + '</p>'


  		





  
  54
  
    
                end


  		





  
  55
  
    
                hgtags << hidden_field_tag(:operation, '', :id => 'repository_operation')


  		





  
  56
  
    
                unless request.post?


  		





  
  57
  
    
                    path = MercurialCreator.access_root_url(MercurialCreator.default_path(@project.identifier))


  		





  
  58
  
    
                    hgtags << javascript_tag("$('repository_url').value = '#{escape_javascript(path)}';")


  		





  
  59
  
    
                end


  		





  
  60
  
    

  		





  
  61
  
    
            elsif @project.repository && @project.repository.created_with_scm &&


  		





  
  62
  
    
                MercurialCreator.enabled? && MercurialCreator.options['url'].present?


  		





  
  63
  
    
                name = MercurialCreator.repository_name(@project.repository.root_url)


  		





  
  64
  
    
                if name


  		





  
  65
  
    
                    if hgtags.include?(l(:text_mercurial_repository_note))


  		





  
  66
  
    
                        hgtags[l(:text_mercurial_repository_note)] = MercurialCreator.external_url(name)


  		





  
  67
  
    
                    elsif hgtags.include?(l(:text_mercurial_repo_example))


  		





  
  68
  
    
                        hgtags[l(:text_mercurial_repo_example)] = MercurialCreator.external_url(name)


  		





  
  69
  
    
                    else


  		





  
  70
  
    
                        hgtags['</p>'] = '<br />' + MercurialCreator.external_url(name) + '</p>'


  		





  
  71
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  72
  
    
                end


  		





  
  73
  
    
            end


  		





  
  74
  
    

  		





  
  75
  
    
            return hgtags


  		





  
  76
  
    
        end


  		





  
  77
  
    

  		





  
  78
  
    
        def bazaar_field_tags_with_add(form, repository)


  		





  
  79
  
    
            bzrtags = bazaar_field_tags_without_add(form, repository)


  		





  
  80
  
    

  		





  
  81
  
    
            if !@project.repository && BazaarCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  82
  
    
                add = submit_tag(l(:button_create_new_repository), :onclick => "$('repository_operation').value = 'add';")


  		





  
  83
  
    
                bzrtags['</p>'] = ' ' + add + '</p>'


  		





  
  84
  
    
                bzrtags << hidden_field_tag(:operation, '', :id => 'repository_operation')


  		





  
  85
  
    
                unless request.post?


  		





  
  86
  
    
                    path = BazaarCreator.access_root_url(BazaarCreator.default_path(@project.identifier))


  		





  
  87
  
    
                    bzrtags << javascript_tag("$('repository_url').value = '#{escape_javascript(path)}';")


  		





  
  88
  
    
                    if BazaarCreator.options['log_encoding']


  		





  
  89
  
    
                        bzrtags << javascript_tag("$('repository_log_encoding').value = '#{escape_javascript(BazaarCreator.options['log_encoding'])}';")


  		





  
  90
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  91
  
    
                end


  		





  
  92
  
    

  		





  
  93
  
    
            elsif @project.repository && @project.repository.created_with_scm &&


  		





  
  94
  
    
                BazaarCreator.enabled? && BazaarCreator.options['url'].present?


  		





  
  95
  
    
                name = BazaarCreator.repository_name(@project.repository.root_url)


  		





  
  96
  
    
                if name


  		





  
  97
  
    
                    bzrtags['</p>'] = '<br />' + BazaarCreator.external_url(name) + '</p>'


  		





  
  98
  
    
                end


  		





  
  99
  
    
            end


  		





  
  100
  
    

  		





  
  101
  
    
            return bzrtags


  		





  
  102
  
    
        end


  		





  
  103
  
    

  		





  
  104
  
    
        def git_field_tags_with_add(form, repository)


  		





  
  105
  
    
            gittags = git_field_tags_without_add(form, repository)


  		





  
  106
  
    

  		





  
  107
  
    
            if !@project.repository && GitCreator.enabled?


  		





  
  108
  
    
                add = submit_tag(l(:button_create_new_repository), :onclick => "$('repository_operation').value = 'add';")


  		





  
  109
  
    
                if gittags.include?('<br />')


  		





  
  110
  
    
                    gittags['<br />'] = ' ' + add + '<br />'


  		





  
  111
  
    
                else


  		





  
  112
  
    
                    gittags['</p>'] = ' ' + add + '</p>'


  		





  
  113
  
    
                end


  		





  
  114
  
    
                gittags << hidden_field_tag(:operation, '', :id => 'repository_operation')


  		





  
  115
  
    
                unless request.post?


  		





  
  116
  
    
                    path = GitCreator.access_root_url(GitCreator.default_path(@project.identifier))


  		





  
  117
  
    
                    gittags << javascript_tag("$('repository_url').value = '#{escape_javascript(path)}';")


  		





  
  118
  
    
                end


  		





  
  119
  
    

  		





  
  120
  
    
            elsif @project.repository && @project.repository.created_with_scm &&


  		





  
  121
  
    
                GitCreator.enabled? && GitCreator.options['url'].present?


  		





  
  122
  
    
                name = GitCreator.repository_name(@project.repository.root_url)


  		





  
  123
  
    
                if name


  		





  
  124
  
    
                    if gittags.include?(l(:text_git_repository_note))


  		





  
  125
  
    
                        gittags[l(:text_git_repository_note)] = GitCreator.external_url(name)


  		





  
  126
  
    
                    elsif gittags.include?(l(:text_git_repo_example))


  		





  
  127
  
    
                        gittags[l(:text_git_repo_example)] = GitCreator.external_url(name)


  		





  
  128
  
    
                    else


  		





  
  129
  
    
                        gittags['</p>'] = '<br />' + GitCreator.external_url(name) + '</p>'


  		





  
  130
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  131
  
    
                end


  		





  
  132
  
    
            end


  		





  
  133
  
    

  		





  
  134
  
    
            return gittags


  		





  
  135
  
    
        end


  		





  
  136

    end

class ContactFormController < ApplicationController


  		





  
  2
  
    
    before_filter :require_login


  		





  
  3
  
    
    before_filter :require_admin, :only => :settings


  		





  
  4
  
    
    before_filter :find_user, :except => [ :preview, :settings ]


  		





  
  5
  
    
    before_filter :check_settings, :except => :settings


  		





  
  6
  
    
    before_filter :find_projects, :except => [ :preview, :settings ]


  		





  
  7
  
    

  		





  
  8
  
    
    helper :custom_fields


  		





  
  9
  
    
    include CustomFieldsHelper


  		





  
  10
  
    

  		





  
  11
  
    
    def index


  		





  
  12
  
    
        @email = Email.new


  		





  
  13
  
    
    end


  		





  
  14
  
    

  		





  
  15
  
    
    def mail


  		





  
  16
  
    
        @email = Email.new(params[:contact_form])


  		





  
  17
  
    
        if @email.valid?


  		





  
  18
  
    
            Mailer.deliver_contact(@user, @email)


  		





  
  19
  
    
            flash[:notice] = l(:notice_contact_email_sent)


  		





  
  20
  
    
            if params[:id]


  		





  
  21
  
    
                redirect_to({ :controller => 'users', :action => 'show', :id => params[:id] })


  		





  
  22
  
    
            else


  		





  
  23
  
    
                redirect_to(:action => 'index')


  		





  
  24
  
    
            end


  		





  
  25
  
    
            return


  		





  
  26
  
    
        end


  		





  
  27
  
    
        render(:action => 'index')


  		





  
  28
  
    
    end


  		





  
  29
  
    

  		





  
  30
  
    
    def preview


  		





  
  31
  
    
        @text = params[:contact_form][:message] if params[:contact_form]


  		





  
  32
  
    
        render(:partial => 'common/preview')


  		





  
  33
  
    
    end


  		





  
  34
  
    

  		





  
  35
  
    
    def settings


  		





  
  36
  
    
        errors = []


  		





  
  37
  
    
        if params[:settings][:contact_us_enabled] &&


  		





  
  38
  
    
            params[:settings][:contact_us_title].blank? &&


  		





  
  39
  
    
            params[:settings][:contact_us_custom_title].blank?


  		





  
  40
  
    
            errors << l(:field_title) + ' ' + l('activerecord.errors.messages.blank')


  		





  
  41
  
    
        end


  		





  
  42
  
    
        if params[:settings][:contact_us_enabled] &&


  		





  
  43
  
    
            params[:settings][:contact_us_recipient].blank?


  		





  
  44
  
    
            if params[:settings][:contact_us_custom_email].blank?


  		





  
  45
  
    
                errors << l(:field_recipient) + ' ' + l('activerecord.errors.messages.blank')


  		





  
  46
  
    
            elsif !params[:settings][:contact_us_custom_email].match(/^([^@\s]+)@((?:[-a-z0-9]+\.)+[a-z]{2,})$/i)


  		





  
  47
  
    
                errors << l(:field_recipient) + ' ' + l('activerecord.errors.messages.invalid')


  		





  
  48
  
    
            end


  		





  
  49
  
    
        end


  		





  
  50
  
    
        if errors.count == 0


  		





  
  51
  
    
            Setting.plugin_contact_form_plugin = params[:settings]


  		





  
  52
  
    
            flash[:notice] = l(:notice_successful_update)


  		





  
  53
  
    
        else


  		





  
  54
  
    
            flash[:error] = errors.join('<br />')


  		





  
  55
  
    
        end


  		





  
  56
  
    
        redirect_to(:controller => 'settings', :tab => 'contact_form')


  		





  
  57
  
    
    end


  		





  
  58
  
    

  		





  
  59
  
    
    def require_login


  		





  
  60
  
    
        Setting.contact_form_requires_login? ? super : true


  		





  
  61
  
    
    end


  		





  
  62
  
    

  		





  
  63
  
    
private


  		





  
  64
  
    

  		





  
  65
  
    
    def check_settings


  		





  
  66
  
    
        if params[:id]


  		





  
  67
  
    
            unless (Setting.users_contact_form? && @user.pref.contact_form) || User.current.admin?


  		





  
  68
  
    
                render_403


  		





  
  69
  
    
                return false


  		





  
  70
  
    
            end


  		





  
  71
  
    
        else


  		





  
  72
  
    
            unless Setting.contact_us_enabled?


  		





  
  73
  
    
                render_403


  		





  
  74
  
    
                return false


  		





  
  75
  
    
            end


  		





  
  76
  
    
        end


  		





  
  77
  
    
    end


  		





  
  78
  
    

  		





  
  79
  
    
    def find_user


  		





  
  80
  
    
        if params[:id]


  		





  
  81
  
    
            @user = User.find(params[:id])


  		





  
  82
  
    
        else


  		





  
  83
  
    
            unless Setting.contact_us_recipient.blank?


  		





  
  84
  
    
                @user = User.find(Setting.contact_us_recipient)


  		





  
  85
  
    
            end


  		





  
  86
  
    
        end


  		





  
  87
  
    
    rescue ActiveRecord::RecordNotFound


  		





  
  88
  
    
        render_404


  		





  
  89
  
    
    end


  		





  
  90
  
    

  		





  
  91
  
    
    def find_projects


  		





  
  92
  
    
        if params[:id]


  		





  
  93
  
    
            @projects = (Project.visible.all & Project.all(:conditions => Project.allowed_to_condition(@user, :view_project))).sort


  		





  
  94
  
    
        else


  		





  
  95
  
    
            @projects = Project.visible.all(:order => 'name')


  		





  
  96
  
    
        end


  		





  
  97
  
    
    end


  		





  
  98
  
    

  		





  
  99
  
    
end

class Email < ActiveRecord::Base


  		





  
  2
  
    
    class_inheritable_accessor :columns


  		





  
  3
  
    

  		





  
  4
  
    
    validates_presence_of :full_name, :reply_to, :if => Proc.new { !User.current.logged? }


  		





  
  5
  
    
    validates_presence_of :subject, :message


  		





  
  6
  
    
    validates_length_of :full_name, :reply_to, :maximum => 60, :if => Proc.new { !User.current.logged? }


  		





  
  7
  
    
    validates_length_of :subject, :maximum => 255


  		





  
  8
  
    
    validates_format_of :full_name, :with => /^[\w\s\'\-\.]*$/i, :if => Proc.new { !User.current.logged? }


  		





  
  9
  
    
    validates_format_of :reply_to, :with => /^([^@\s]+)@((?:[-a-z0-9]+\.)+[a-z]{2,})$/i, :if => Proc.new { !User.current.logged? }


  		





  
  10
  
    

  		





  
  11
  
    
    acts_as_customizable


  		





  
  12
  
    

  		





  
  13
  
    
    self.columns = []


  		





  
  14
  
    

  		





  
  15
  
    
    def full_name


  		





  
  16
  
    
        User.current.logged? ? User.current : @full_name


  		





  
  17
  
    
    end


  		





  
  18
  
    

  		





  
  19
  
    
    def full_name=(arg)


  		





  
  20
  
    
        @full_name = arg


  		





  
  21
  
    
    end


  		





  
  22
  
    

  		





  
  23
  
    
    def reply_to


  		





  
  24
  
    
        User.current.logged? ? User.current.mail : @reply_to


  		





  
  25
  
    
    end


  		





  
  26
  
    

  		





  
  27
  
    
    def reply_to=(arg)


  		





  
  28
  
    
        @reply_to = arg


  		





  
  29
  
    
    end


  		





  
  30
  
    

  		





  
  31
  
    
    def subject


  		





  
  32
  
    
        @subject


  		





  
  33
  
    
    end


  		





  
  34
  
    

  		





  
  35
  
    
    def subject=(arg)


  		





  
  36
  
    
        @subject = arg


  		





  
  37
  
    
    end


  		





  
  38
  
    

  		





  
  39
  
    
    def project


  		





  
  40
  
    
        @project


  		





  
  41
  
    
    end


  		





  
  42
  
    

  		





  
  43
  
    
    def project_id

        @project.id if @project


  		





  
  45
  
    
    end


  		





  
  46

    end

    end

        def contact(user, email)


  		





  
  19
  
    
            message_id(email)


  		





  
  20
  
    

  		





  
  21
  
    
            from("#{email.full_name} <#{email.reply_to}>")


  		





  
  22
  
    
            reply_to("#{email.full_name} <#{email.reply_to}>")


  		





  
  23
  
    
            recipients(user ? "#{user} <#{user.mail}>" : Setting.contact_us_email)


  		





  
  24
  
    
            subject(email.subject)


  		





  
  25
  
    

  		





  
  26
  
    
            body(:project => email.project, :message => email.message, :custom_values => email.custom_field_values)

  29
  
    
        end

        # Modified: def render_multipart(method_name, body)


  		





  
  32
  
    
        def render_email(body)


  		





  
  33
  
    
            if Setting.plain_text_mail?


  		





  
  34
  
    
                content_type('text/plain')


  		





  
  35
  
    
                body(render(:file => 'email.text.plain.rhtml', :body => body, :layout => 'contact.text.plain.rhtml'))


  		





  
  36
  
    
            else


  		





  
  37
  
    
                content_type('multipart/alternative')


  		





  
  38
  
    
                part(:content_type => "text/plain", :body => render(:file => 'email.text.plain.rhtml', :body => body, :layout => 'contact.text.plain.rhtml'))


  		





  
  39
  
    
                part(:content_type => "text/html", :body => render(:file => 'email.text.html.rhtml', :body => body, :layout => 'contact.text.html.rhtml'))


  		





  
  40
  
    
            end


  		





  
  41
  
    
        end


  		





  
  42
  
    

  		





  
  43
  
    
    end

            def self.plugin_contact_form_plugin=(v)


  		





  
  37
  
    
                setting = find_or_default('plugin_contact_form_plugin')


  		





  
  38
  
    
                setting.value = (v ? v : '')


  		





  
  39
  
    
                @cached_settings['plugin_contact_form_plugin'] = nil if @cached_settings


  		





  
  40
  
    
                Rails.cache.delete("chiliproject/setting/plugin_contact_form_plugin")


  		





  
  41
  
    
                setting.save(false)

                setting.value


  		





  
  43
  
    
            end

    def find_custom_field_template(custom_field)


  		





  
  4
  
    
        filename = custom_field.name.gsub(%r{[^a-z0-9_]+}i, '_').downcase


  		





  
  5
  
    
        filename.gsub!(%r{(^_+|_+$)}, '')


  		





  
  6
  
    

  		





  
  7
  
    
        unless filename.empty?


  		





  
  8
  
    
            self.view_paths.each do |load_path|


  		





  
  9
  
    
                if template = load_path["custom_values/#{custom_field.field_format}/_#{filename}"]


  		





  
  10
  
    
                    return "custom_values/#{custom_field.field_format}/#{filename}"


  		





  
  11
  
    
                end


  		





  
  12
  
    
            end


  		





  
  13
  
    

  		





  
  14
  
    
            self.view_paths.each do |load_path|


  		





  
  15
  
    
                if template = load_path["custom_values/common/_#{custom_field.field_format}"]


  		





  
  16
  
    
                    return "custom_values/common/#{custom_field.field_format}"


  		





  
  17
  
    
                end


  		





  
  18
  
    
            end


  		





  
  19
  
    
        end


  		





  
  20
  
    

  		





  
  21
  
    
        nil


  		





  
  22
  
    
    end

    def custom_value_for_user(name, user = User.current)


  		





  
  25
  
    
        custom_field = CustomField.find_by_name_and_type(name, 'UserCustomField')


  		





  
  26
  
    
        if custom_field


  		





  
  27
  
    
            custom_value = user.custom_value_for(custom_field)


  		





  
  28
  
    
            if custom_value && !custom_value.value.blank?


  		





  
  29
  
    
                custom_value


  		





  
  30
  
    
            else


  		





  
  31
  
    
                nil


  		





  
  32
  
    
            end


  		





  
  33
  
    
        else


  		





  
  34
  
    
            nil


  		





  
  35
  
    
        end


  		





  
  36
  
    
    end

    def extended_column_content(column, object)


  		





  
  39
  
    
        value = column.value(object)


  		





  
  40
  
    

  		





  
  41
  
    
        case object


  		





  
  42
  
    
        when User


  		





  
  43
  
    
            case column.name


  		





  
  44
  
    
            when :login


  		





  
  45
  
    
                return (avatar(object, :size => 14) || '') + link_to(h(value), :action => 'edit', :id => object)


  		





  
  46
  
    
            when :mail


  		





  
  47
  
    
                return mail_to(h(value))


  		





  
  48
  
    
            when :status


  		





  
  49
  
    
                return h(l("status_" + %w(anonymous active registered locked)[value]))


  		





  
  50
  
    
            when :language


  		





  
  51
  
    
                language = valid_languages.detect{ |lang| lang.to_s == value }


  		





  
  52
  
    
                return h(ll(language.to_s, :general_lang_name))


  		





  
  53
  
    
            end


  		





  
  54
  
    
        when Project


  		





  
  55
  
    
            case column.name


  		





  
  56
  
    
            when :project


  		





  
  57
  
    
                return content_tag(:span, link_to_project(object, { :action => 'settings' }, :title => object.short_description))


  		





  
  58
  
    
            when :description


  		





  
  59
  
    
                return textilizable(object.short_description, :project => object)


  		





  
  60
  
    
            when :created_on


  		





  
  61
  
    
                return format_date(value)


  		





  
  62
  
    
            when :homepage


  		





  
  63
  
    
                return link_to(h(value), value)


  		





  
  64
  
    
            when :active


  		





  
  65
  
    
                return checked_image(object.status == 1)


  		





  
  66
  
    
            end


  		





  
  67
  
    
        end


  		





  
  68
  
    

  		





  
  69
  
    
        case value


  		





  
  70
  
    
        when CustomValue


  		





  
  71
  
    
            return show_value(value)


  		





  
  72
  
    
        when User


  		





  
  73
  
    
            return link_to_user(value)


  		





  
  74
  
    
        when Project


  		





  
  75
  
    
            return link_to_project(value)


  		





  
  76
  
    
        when Version


  		





  
  77
  
    
            return link_to(h(value), :controller => 'versions', :action => 'show', :id => value)


  		





  
  78
  
    
        when Issue


  		





  
  79
  
    
            return link_to_issue(value, :subject => false)


  		





  
  80
  
    
        when Time


  		





  
  81
  
    
            return format_time(value)


  		





  
  82
  
    
        when Date


  		





  
  83
  
    
            return format_date(value)


  		





  
  84
  
    
        when TrueClass


  		





  
  85
  
    
            return checked_image(value)


  		





  
  86
  
    
        when FalseClass


  		





  
  87
  
    
            return nil


  		





  
  88
  
    
        else


  		





  
  89
  
    
            return h(value)


  		





  
  90
  
    
        end


  		





  
  91
  
    
    end


  		





  
  92
  
    

  		





  
  93
  
    
end

class UserListSetting < ActiveRecord::Base


  		





  
  2
  
    
    belongs_to :user


  		





  
  3
  
    

  		





  
  4
  
    
    SUPPORTED_LISTS = [ 'users', 'projects' ]


  		





  
  5
  
    

  		





  
  6
  
    
    serialize :columns, Array


  		





  
  7
  
    

  		





  
  8
  
    
    validates_presence_of :user, :list, :columns


  		





  
  9
  
    
    validates_uniqueness_of :user_id, :scope => :list


  		





  
  10
  
    
    validates_inclusion_of :list, :in => SUPPORTED_LISTS


  		





  
  11
  
    

  		





  
  12
  
    
    def initialize(attributes = nil)


  		





  
  13
  
    
        super


  		





  
  14
  
    
        self.columns ||= list_class.default_columns


  		





  
  15
  
    
    end


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
    def list_class


  		





  
  18
  
    
        case list


  		





  
  19
  
    
        when 'users'


  		





  
  20
  
    
            User


  		





  
  21
  
    
        when 'projects'


  		





  
  22
  
    
            Project


  		





  
  23
  
    
        end


  		





  
  24
  
    
    end


  		





  
  25
  
    

  		





  
  26
  
    
    def columns=(fields)


  		





  
  27
  
    
        if fields.is_a?(Array)


  		





  
  28
  
    
            write_attribute(:columns, fields.collect{ |field| field.is_a?(ExtendedColumn) ? field.name.to_sym : field.to_sym })


  		





  
  29
  
    
        else


  		





  
  30
  
    
            self.columns = [ fields ]


  		





  
  31
  
    
        end


  		





  
  32
  
    
        remove_instance_variable(:@extended_columns) if instance_variable_defined?(:@extended_columns)


  		





  
  33
  
    
    end


  		





  
  34
  
    

  		





  
  35
  
    
    def columns


  		





  
  36
  
    
        if @extended_columns


  		





  
  37
  
    
            @extended_columns


  		





  
  38
  
    
        else


  		





  
  39
  
    
            fields = read_attribute(:columns) || list_class.default_columns.collect{ |column| column.name }


  		





  
  40
  
    

  		





  
  41
  
    
            available_columns = list_class.available_columns.inject({}) do |hash, column|


  		





  
  42
  
    
                hash[column.name] = column


  		





  
  43
  
    
                hash


  		





  
  44
  
    
            end


  		





  
  45
  
    

  		





  
  46
  
    
            @extended_columns = fields.inject([]) do |array, field|


  		





  
  47
  
    
                if available_columns[field.to_sym]


  		





  
  48
  
    
                    array << available_columns[field.to_sym]


  		





  
  49
  
    
                end


  		





  
  50
  
    
                array


  		





  
  51
  
    
            end


  		





  
  52
  
    
        end


  		





  
  53
  
    
    end


  		





  
  54
  
    

  		





  
  55
  
    
end

    def value(object)

  22
  
    
                @value.call(object)


  		





  
  23

  24
  
    
                object.send(@value)


  		





  
  25
  
    
            end


  		





  
  26
  
    
        elsif object.respond_to?(name)


  		





  
  27
  
    
            object.send(name)

        end

    end

        def custom_field_tag_with_extended(name, custom_value)


  		





  
  39
  
    
            custom_field = custom_value.custom_field


  		





  
  40
  
    
            field_name   = "#{name}[custom_field_values][#{custom_field.id}]"


  		





  
  41
  
    
            field_id     = "#{name}_custom_field_values_#{custom_field.id}"


  		





  
  42
  
    
            field_title  = custom_field.name.gsub(%r{[^a-z0-9_]+}i, '_').downcase


  		





  
  43
  
    
            field_class  = (field_title =~ %r{[a-z0-9]+}i) ? "#{name}_custom_field_values_#{field_title}" : field_id


  		





  
  44
  
    
            field_format = Redmine::CustomFieldFormat.find_by_name(custom_field.field_format)


  		





  
  45
  
    

  		





  
  46
  
    
            case field_format.try(:edit_as)


  		





  
  47
  
    
            when 'string', 'link'


  		





  
  48
  
    
                tag = text_field_tag(field_name, custom_value.value, :id => field_id, :class => field_class)


  		





  
  49
  
    
            when 'project'


  		





  
  50
  
    
                blank = custom_field.is_required? ?


  		





  
  51
  
    
                       (custom_field.default_value.blank? ? content_tag(:option, "--- #{l(:actionview_instancetag_blank_option)} ---") : '') :


  		





  
  52
  
    
                        content_tag(:option)


  		





  
  53
  
    
                tag = select_tag(field_name,


  		





  
  54
  
    
                                 blank + options_for_select(custom_field.possible_values_options(custom_value.customized), custom_value.value),


  		





  
  55
  
    
                                 :id => field_id, :class => field_class)


  		





  
  56
  
    
            else


  		





  
  57
  
    
                tag = custom_field_tag_without_extended(name, custom_value)


  		





  
  58
  
    
            end


  		





  
  59
  
    

  		





  
  60
  
    
            unless custom_field.hint.blank?


  		





  
  61
  
    
                tag << '<br />'

                tag << content_tag(:em, h(custom_field.hint))


  		





  
  63

    def self.included(base)

  17

  19
  
    
            case value.class.name

  21
  
    
                h(show_value(value))


  		





  
  22

  23
  
    
                column_content_without_extended(column, issue)


  		





  
  24

  6

    end

  11

  16
  
    
            end

        def add_available_column(column)


  		





  
  48
  
    
            @@available_columns << column if column.is_a?(ExtendedColumn)


  		





  
  49
  
    
            remove_class_variable(:@@available_columns_cache) if class_variable_defined?(:@@available_columns_cache)


  		





  
  50
  
    
        end


  		





  
  51
  
    

  		





  
  52
  
    
        def default_columns


  		





  
  53
  
    
            @@available_columns.select do |column|


  		





  
  54
  
    
                case column.name


  		





  
  55
  
    
                when :login, :firstname, :lastname, :mail, :admin, :created_on, :last_login_on


  		





  
  56
  
    
                    true


  		





  
  57
  
    
                else


  		





  
  58
  
    
                    false


  		





  
  59
  
    
                end


  		





  
  60
  
    
            end


  		





  
  61
  
    
        end


  		





  
  62
  
    

  		





  
  63
  
    
    end


  		





  
  64
  
    

  		





  
  65
  
    
end


  		












  

    
      b/vendor/plugins/extended_fields/lib/extended_users_controller_patch.rb

require_dependency 'users_controller'

    def self.included(base)


  		





  
  6
  
    
        base.send(:include, InstanceMethods)


  		





  
  7
  
    
        base.class_eval do


  		





  
  8
  
    
            unloadable


  		





  
  9
  
    

  		





  
  10
  
    
            before_filter :find_settings, :only => :index


  		





  
  11
  
    

  		





  
  12
  
    
            alias_method_chain :index, :extended


  		





  
  13
  
    
        end


  		





  
  14
  
    
    end

    module InstanceMethods


  		





  
  17
  
    

  		





  
  18
  
    
        def index_with_extended


  		





  
  19
  
    
            index_without_extended


  		





  
  20
  
    

  		





  
  21
  
    
            if params[:save] == '1'


  		





  
  22
  
    
                @list_settings.save


  		





  
  23
  
    
            end


  		





  
  24
  
    
        end

    private

        def find_settings


  		





  
  29
  
    
            @list_settings = UserListSetting.find_by_user_id_and_list(User.current.id, 'users')


  		





  
  30
  
    
            @list_settings = UserListSetting.new(:user_id => User.current.id, :list => 'users') unless @list_settings


  		





  
  31
  
    
            @list_settings.columns = params[:c] if params[:c]


  		





  
  32
  
    
        end


  		





  
  33
  
    

  		





  
  34
  
    
    end

class MigrateExtendedProfile < ActiveRecord::Migration


  		





  
  2
  
    

  		





  
  3
  
    
    def self.up


  		





  
  4
  
    
        pos = UserCustomField.maximum(:position) || 0


  		





  
  5
  
    
        settings = Setting.respond_to?(:plugin_extended_profile_plugin) ? Setting.plugin_extended_profile_plugin : nil


  		





  
  6
  
    

  		





  
  7
  
    
        company      = UserCustomField.create(:name => 'Company',             :field_format => 'string',  :position => pos += 1, :is_for_new => false, :searchable => true)


  		





  
  8
  
    
        company_site = UserCustomField.create(:name => 'Company website',     :field_format => 'link',    :position => pos += 1, :is_for_new => false)


  		





  
  9
  
    
        position     = UserCustomField.create(:name => 'Position',            :field_format => 'string',  :position => pos += 1, :is_for_new => false, :searchable => true)


  		





  
  10
  
    
        project      = UserCustomField.create(:name => 'Project of interest', :field_format => 'project', :position => pos += 1, :searchable => true,  :is_required => (settings && settings[:require_project]) ? true : false)


  		





  
  11
  
    
        website      = UserCustomField.create(:name => 'Personal website',    :field_format => 'link',    :position => pos += 1, :is_for_new => false)


  		





  
  12
  
    
        blog         = UserCustomField.create(:name => 'Blog',                :field_format => 'link',    :position => pos += 1, :is_for_new => false)


  		





  
  13
  
    
        facebook     = UserCustomField.create(:name => 'Facebook',            :field_format => 'string',  :position => pos += 1, :is_for_new => false, :regexp => '^([0-9]+|[A-Za-z0-9.]+)$', :hint => 'e.g. 100000066953233 or andriy.lesyuk')


  		





  
  14
  
    
        twitter      = UserCustomField.create(:name => 'Twitter',             :field_format => 'string',  :position => pos += 1, :is_for_new => false, :regexp => '^@?[A-Za-z0-9_]+$',        :hint => 'e.g. AndriyLesyuk')


  		





  
  15
  
    
        linkedin     = UserCustomField.create(:name => 'LinkedIn',            :field_format => 'link',    :position => pos += 1, :is_for_new => false)


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
        if project.has_attribute?(:visible)


  		





  
  18
  
    
            project.update_attribute(:visible, false)


  		





  
  19
  
    
        end


  		





  
  20
  
    

  		





  
  21
  
    
        if ActiveRecord::Base.connection.table_exists?('extended_profiles')


  		





  
  22
  
    
            User.connection.select_all("SELECT user_id, company, company_site, position, project_id, personal_site, blog, facebook, twitter, linkedin


  		





  
  23
  
    
                                        FROM extended_profiles").each do |profile|


  		





  
  24
  
    
                if user = User.find_by_id(profile['user_id'])


  		





  
  25
  
    
                    CustomValue.create(:custom_field => company,      :customized => user, :value => profile['company'])       if profile['company'].present?


  		





  
  26
  
    
                    CustomValue.create(:custom_field => company_site, :customized => user, :value => profile['company_site'])  if profile['company_site'].present?


  		





  
  27
  
    
                    CustomValue.create(:custom_field => position,     :customized => user, :value => profile['position'])      if profile['position'].present?


  		





  
  28
  
    
                    CustomValue.create(:custom_field => project,      :customized => user, :value => profile['project_id'])    if profile['project_id'].present?


  		





  
  29
  
    
                    CustomValue.create(:custom_field => website,      :customized => user, :value => profile['personal_site']) if profile['personal_site'].present?


  		





  
  30
  
    
                    CustomValue.create(:custom_field => blog,         :customized => user, :value => profile['blog'])          if profile['blog'].present?


  		





  
  31
  
    
                    CustomValue.create(:custom_field => facebook,     :customized => user, :value => profile['facebook'])      if profile['facebook'].present?


  		





  
  32
  
    
                    CustomValue.create(:custom_field => twitter,      :customized => user, :value => profile['twitter'])       if profile['twitter'].present?


  		





  
  33
  
    
                    CustomValue.create(:custom_field => linkedin,     :customized => user, :value => profile['linkedin'])      if profile['linkedin'].present?


  		





  
  34
  
    
                end


  		





  
  35
  
    
            end


  		





  
  36
  
    
        end


  		





  
  37
  
    
    end


  		





  
  38
  
    

  		





  
  39
  
    
end


  		












  

    
      b/vendor/plugins/extended_profile/db/migrate/102_fix_missing_project.rb

class FixMissingProject < ActiveRecord::Migration


  		





  
  2
  
    

  		





  
  3
  
    
    def self.up


  		





  
  4
  
    
        custom_field = CustomField.find_by_name_and_type('Project of interest', 'UserCustomField')


  		





  
  5
  
    
        if custom_field.is_required?


  		





  
  6
  
    
            User.find(:all, :conditions => { :type => 'User' }).each do |user|


  		





  
  7
  
    
                interest_project = user.custom_field_values.detect{ |custom_value| custom_value.custom_field_id == custom_field.id }


  		





  
  8
  
    
                if interest_project && interest_project.value.nil?


  		





  
  9
  
    
                    project = (user.memberships.collect(&:project).first || Project.all(:conditions => Project.allowed_to_condition(user, :view_project), :order => 'name').first)


  		





  
  10
  
    
                    if project


  		





  
  11
  
    
                        interest_project.value = project.id


  		





  
  12
  
    
                        interest_project.save


  		





  
  13
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  14
  
    
                end


  		





  
  15
  
    
            end


  		





  
  16
  
    
        end


  		





  
  17
  
    
    end


  		





  
  18
  
    

  		





  
  19
  
    
end

        def fixed_open_id_authenticate(openid_url)


  		





  
  65
  
    
            options = [ :nickname, :fullname, :email ]


  		





  
  66
  
    

  		





  
  67
  
    
            # Google OpenID


  		





  
  68
  
    
            options << OPENID_AX_EMAIL     # mail


  		





  
  69
  
    
            options << OPENID_AX_FIRSTNAME # firstname


  		





  
  70
  
    
            options << OPENID_AX_LASTNAME  # lastname


  		





  
  71
  
    
            options << OPENID_AX_LANGUAGE  # language


  		





  
  72
  
    

  		





  
  73
  
    
            authenticate_with_open_id(openid_url, :required => options, :return_to => signin_url) do |result, identity_url, registration|


  		





  
  74
  
    
                if result.successful?


  		





  
  75
  
    
                    user = User.find_or_initialize_by_identity_url(identity_url)


  		





  
  76
  
    
                    if user.new_record?


  		





  
  77
  
    
                        redirect_to(home_url) && return unless Setting.self_registration?


  		





  
  78
  
    

  		





  
  79
  
    
                        if registration[OPENID_AX_EMAIL]


  		





  
  80
  
    
                            user.login = registration[OPENID_AX_EMAIL].first


  		





  
  81
  
    
                            user.mail = registration[OPENID_AX_EMAIL].first


  		





  
  82
  
    
                        else


  		





  
  83
  
    
                            user.login = registration['nickname'] unless registration['nickname'].nil?


  		





  
  84
  
    
                            user.mail = registration['email'] unless registration['email'].nil?


  		





  
  85
  
    
                        end


  		





  
  86
  
    
                        user.firstname, user.lastname = registration['fullname'].split(' ') unless registration['fullname'].nil?


  		





  
  87
  
    
                        if registration[OPENID_AX_FIRSTNAME]


  		





  
  88
  
    
                            user.firstname = registration[OPENID_AX_FIRSTNAME].first


  		





  
  89
  
    
                        end


  		





  
  90
  
    
                        if registration[OPENID_AX_LASTNAME]


  		





  
  91
  
    
                            user.lastname = registration[OPENID_AX_LASTNAME].first


  		





  
  92
  
    
                        end


  		





  
  93
  
    
                        if registration[OPENID_AX_LANGUAGE]


  		





  
  94
  
    
                            lang = registration[OPENID_AX_LANGUAGE].first


  		





  
  95
  
    
                            if lang


  		





  
  96
  
    
                                language = find_language(lang) || find_language(lang.split('-').first)


  		





  
  97
  
    
                                if language


  		





  
  98
  
    
                                    user.language = language.to_s


  		





  
  99
  
    
                                    set_language_if_valid(language)


  		





  
  100
  
    
                                end


  		





  
  101
  
    
                            end


  		





  
  102
  
    
                        end


  		





  
  103
  
    
                        user.random_password


  		





  
  104
  
    
                        user.register


  		





  
  105
  
    

  		





  
  106
  
    
                        case Setting.self_registration


  		





  
  107
  
    
                        when '2'


  		





  
  108
  
    
                            register_manually_by_administrator(user) do


  		





  
  109
  
    
                                onthefly_creation_failed(user)


  		





  
  110
  
    
                            end


  		





  
  111
  
    
                        else


  		





  
  112
  
    
                            register_automatically(user) do


  		





  
  113
  
    
                                onthefly_creation_failed(user)


  		





  
  114
  
    
                            end


  		





  
  115
  
    
                        end


  		





  
  116
  
    
                    else


  		





  
  117
  
    
                        if user.active?


  		





  
  118
  
    
                            successful_authentication(user)


  		





  
  119
  
    
                        else


  		





  
  120
  
    
                            account_pending


  		





  
  121
  
    
                        end


  		





  
  122
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  123
  
    
                end


  		





  
  124
  
    
            end


  		





  
  125
  
    
        end


  		





  
  126
  
    

  		





  
  127
  
    
    end


  		





  
  128
  
    

  		





  
  129
  
    
end

class RemovalController < ApplicationController


  		





  
  2
  
    
    layout 'admin'


  		





  
  3
  
    

  		





  
  4
  
    
    before_filter :find_project


  		





  
  5
  
    
    before_filter :find_redirect


  		





  
  6
  
    
    before_filter :require_admin


  		





  
  7
  
    

  		





  
  8
  
    
    def edit


  		





  
  9
  
    
    end


  		





  
  10
  
    

  		





  
  11
  
    
    def update


  		





  
  12
  
    
        if @redirect


  		





  
  13
  
    
            if params[:redirect][:redirect_type] == 'no_redirect' && params[:redirect][:message].empty?


  		





  
  14
  
    
                @redirect.destroy


  		





  
  15
  
    
                flash[:notice] = l(:notice_successful_delete)


  		





  
  16
  
    
                @redirect = nil


  		





  
  17
  
    
            else


  		





  
  18
  
    
                if @redirect.update_attributes(params[:redirect])


  		





  
  19
  
    
                    flash[:notice] = l(:notice_successful_update)


  		





  
  20
  
    
                end


  		





  
  21
  
    
            end


  		





  
  22
  
    
        else


  		





  
  23
  
    
            attributes = params[:redirect].dup


  		





  
  24
  
    
            @redirect = ProjectRedirect.new(attributes.merge(:project => @project))


  		





  
  25
  
    
            if @redirect.save


  		





  
  26
  
    
                flash[:notice] = l(:notice_successful_create)


  		





  
  27
  
    
            end


  		





  
  28
  
    
        end


  		





  
  29
  
    
        render(:action => 'edit')


  		





  
  30
  
    
    end


  		





  
  31
  
    

  		





  
  32
  
    
    def preview


  		





  
  33
  
    
        @text = params[:redirect][:message]


  		





  
  34
  
    
        render(:partial => 'common/preview')


  		





  
  35
  
    
    end


  		





  
  36

private


  		





  
  38
  
    

  		





  
  39
  
    
    def find_project


  		





  
  40
  
    
        @project = Project.find(params[:id])


  		





  
  41
  
    
        render_403 if @project.active?


  		





  
  42
  
    
    rescue ActiveRecord::RecordNotFound


  		





  
  43
  
    
        render_404


  		





  
  44
  
    
    end

    end


  		





  
  49
  
    

  		





  
  50
  
    
end

class ProjectRedirect < ActiveRecord::Base


  		





  
  2
  
    
    belongs_to :project


  		





  
  3
  
    

  		





  
  4
  
    
    validates_presence_of :project, :redirect_type


  		





  
  5
  
    
    validates_uniqueness_of :project_id


  		





  
  6
  
    
    validates_inclusion_of :redirect_type, :in => %w(no_redirect to_url to_redmine)


  		





  
  7
  
    
    validates_length_of :url, :maximum => 255, :allow_nil => true


  		





  
  8
  
    
    validates_format_of :url, :with => /^https?:\/\//i, :if => Proc.new { |redirect| !redirect.url.blank? }


  		





  
  9
  
    
    validates_numericality_of :delay, :only_integer => true, :allow_nil => true


  		





  
  10
  
    

  		





  
  11
  
    
    def url=(arg)


  		





  
  12
  
    
        if redirect_type == 'to_url'


  		





  
  13
  
    
            write_attribute(:url, arg)


  		





  
  14
  
    
        end


  		





  
  15
  
    
    end


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
    def base_url=(arg)


  		





  
  18
  
    
        if redirect_type == 'to_redmine'


  		





  
  19
  
    
            write_attribute(:url, arg)


  		





  
  20
  
    
        end


  		





  
  21
  
    
    end


  		





  
  22
  
    

  		





  
  23
  
    
    def base_url


  		





  
  24
  
    
        url


  		





  
  25
  
    
    end


  		





  
  26
  
    

  		





  
  27
  
    
    def delay=(arg)


  		





  
  28
  
    
        if redirect_type == 'to_url' || redirect_type == 'to_redmine'


  		





  
  29
  
    
            write_attribute(:delay, arg)


  		





  
  30
  
    
        else


  		





  
  31
  
    
            write_attribute(:delay, nil)


  		





  
  32
  
    
        end


  		





  
  33
  
    
    end


  		





  
  34
  
    

  		





  
  35
  
    
protected


  		





  
  36
  
    

  		





  
  37
  
    
    def validate


  		





  
  38
  
    
        if redirect_type == 'to_url' || redirect_type == 'to_redmine'


  		





  
  39
  
    
            errors.add(:url, :must_be_present_for_this_type) unless url.present?


  		





  
  40
  
    
        end


  		





  
  41
  
    
    end


  		





  
  42
  
    

  		





  
  43
  
    
end

  7
  
    
    unless ProjectsController.included_modules.include?(RemovalProjectsControllerPatch)

        ProjectsController.send(:include, RemovalProjectsControllerPatch)


  		





  
  9
  
    
    end


  		





  
  10
  
    
    unless ApplicationController.included_modules.include?(RemovalApplicationControllerPatch)


  		





  
  11

  12

require_dependency 'application_controller'


  		





  
  2
  
    

  		





  
  3
  
    
module RemovalApplicationControllerPatch


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
    def self.included(base)


  		





  
  6
  
    
        base.extend(ClassMethods)


  		





  
  7
  
    
        base.send(:include, InstanceMethods)


  		





  
  8
  
    
        base.class_eval do


  		





  
  9
  
    
            unloadable


  		





  
  10
  
    
            alias_method_chain :authorize, :removal


  		





  
  11
  
    
        end


  		





  
  12
  
    
    end


  		





  
  13
  
    

  		





  
  14
  
    
    module ClassMethods


  		





  
  15
  
    
    end


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
    module InstanceMethods


  		





  
  18
  
    

  		





  
  19
  
    
        def authorize_with_removal(ctrl = params[:controller], action = params[:action], global = false)


  		





  
  20
  
    
            if @project && !@project.active?


  		





  
  21
  
    
                @redirect = ProjectRedirect.find_by_project_id(@project.id)


  		





  
  22
  
    
                if @redirect


  		





  
  23
  
    
                    @redirect_url = @redirect.url


  		





  
  24
  
    
                    if @redirect.redirect_type == 'to_redmine'


  		





  
  25
  
    
                        url = url_for(:only_path => true)


  		





  
  26
  
    
                        if ENV['RAILS_RELATIVE_URL_ROOT'].present? && url.index(ENV['RAILS_RELATIVE_URL_ROOT']) == 0


  		





  
  27
  
    
                            url.sub!(ENV['RAILS_RELATIVE_URL_ROOT'], '')


  		





  
  28
  
    
                        end


  		





  
  29
  
    
                        @redirect_url << url


  		





  
  30
  
    
                    end


  		





  
  31
  
    
                    render(:template => 'common/redirect')


  		





  
  32
  
    
                else


  		





  
  33
  
    
                    authorize_without_removal(ctrl, action, global)


  		





  
  34
  
    
                end


  		





  
  35
  
    
            else


  		





  
  36
  
    
                authorize_without_removal(ctrl, action, global)


  		





  
  37
  
    
            end


  		





  
  38
  
    
        end


  		





  
  39
  
    

  		





  
  40
  
    
    end


  		





  
  41
  
    

  		





  
  42
  
    
end

require_dependency 'projects_controller'


  		





  
  2
  
    

  		





  
  3
  
    
module RemovalProjectsControllerPatch


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
    def self.included(base)


  		





  
  6
  
    
        base.extend(ClassMethods)


  		





  
  7
  
    
        base.send(:include, InstanceMethods)


  		





  
  8
  
    
        base.class_eval do


  		





  
  9
  
    
            unloadable


  		





  
  10
  
    
            alias_method :archive, :archive_with_removal


  		





  
  11
  
    
        end


  		





  
  12
  
    
    end


  		





  
  13
  
    

  		





  
  14
  
    
    module ClassMethods


  		





  
  15
  
    
    end


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
    module InstanceMethods


  		





  
  18
  
    

  		





  
  19
  
    
        def archive_with_removal


  		





  
  20
  
    
            if request.post?


  		





  
  21
  
    
                unless @project.archive


  		





  
  22
  
    
                    flash[:error] = l(:error_can_not_archive_project)


  		





  
  23
  
    
                end


  		





  
  24
  
    
            end


  		





  
  25
  
    
            redirect_to(url_for(:controller => 'removal', :action => 'edit', :id => @project))


  		





  
  26
  
    
        end


  		





  
  27
  
    

  		





  
  28
  
    
        # TODO: clean on unarchive


  		





  
  29
  
    
    end


  		





  
  30
  
    

  		





  
  31
  
    
end
