  5
  
    

  		





  
  6
  
    
Dispatcher.to_prepare :project_settings_hook_plugin do


  		





  
  7
  
    
    unless ProjectsHelper.included_modules.include?(SettingsProjectsHelperPatch)

        ProjectsHelper.send(:include, SettingsProjectsHelperPatch)


  		





  
  9
  
    
    end

end

require_dependency 'projects_helper'


  		





  
  2

module SettingsProjectsHelperPatch


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
    def self.included(base)


  		





  
  6
  
    
        base.extend(ClassMethods)


  		





  
  7
  
    
        base.send(:include, InstanceMethods)


  		





  
  8
  
    
        base.class_eval do


  		





  
  9
  
    
            unloadable


  		





  
  10
  
    
            alias_method_chain :project_settings_tabs, :hook


  		





  
  11
  
    
        end


  		





  
  12
  
    
    end


  		





  
  13
  
    

  		





  
  14
  
    
    module ClassMethods


  		





  
  15
  
    
    end


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
    module InstanceMethods


  		





  
  18
  
    

  		





  
  19
  
    
        def project_settings_tabs_with_hook


  		





  
  20
  
    
            tabs = project_settings_tabs_without_hook


  		





  
  21
  
    
            call_hook(:helper_projects_settings_tabs, { :tabs => tabs })


  		





  
  22
  
    
            return tabs


  		





  
  23
  
    
        end


  		





  
  24
  
    

  		





  
  25
  
    
    end


  		





  
  26
  
    

  		





  
  27
  
    
end

= reCAPTCHA


  		





  
  2
  
    

  		





  
  3
  
    
Author::    Jason L Perry (http://ambethia.com)


  		





  
  4
  
    
Copyright:: Copyright (c) 2007 Jason L Perry


  		





  
  5
  
    
License::   {MIT}[http://creativecommons.org/licenses/MIT/]


  		





  
  6
  
    
Info::      http://ambethia.com/recaptcha


  		





  
  7
  
    
Git::       http://github.com/ambethia/recaptcha/tree/master


  		





  
  8
  
    
Bugs::      http://github.com/ambethia/recaptcha/issues


  		





  
  9
  
    

  		





  
  10
  
    
This plugin adds helpers for the {reCAPTCHA API}[http://recaptcha.net]. In your


  		





  
  11
  
    
views you can use the +recaptcha_tags+ method to embed the needed javascript,


  		





  
  12
  
    
and you can validate in your controllers with +verify_recaptcha+.


  		





  
  13
  
    

  		





  
  14
  
    
Beforehand you need to configure Recaptcha with your custom private and public


  		





  
  15
  
    
key. You may find detailed examples below. Exceptions will be raised if you


  		





  
  16
  
    
call these methods and the keys can't be found.


  		





  
  17
  
    

  		





  
  18
  
    
== About this fork


  		





  
  19
  
    

  		





  
  20
  
    
This fork tries to introduce a more convenient way to configure recaptcha's


  		





  
  21
  
    
settings. The API will be inspired by {Thoughtbot's


  		





  
  22
  
    
Hoptoad}[http://robots.thoughtbot.com/post/344833329/mygem-configure-block].


  		





  
  23
  
    

  		





  
  24
  
    
== Rails Installation


  		





  
  25
  
    

  		





  
  26
  
    
reCAPTCHA for Rails > 3.0, add this to your Gemfile:


  		





  
  27
  
    

  		





  
  28
  
    
  gem "recaptcha", :require => "recaptcha/rails"


  		





  
  29
  
    

  		





  
  30
  
    
Rails apps below 3.0 are no longer supported, but you can install an older


  		





  
  31
  
    
release and view it's README.


  		





  
  32
  
    

  		





  
  33
  
    
== Setting up your API Keys


  		





  
  34
  
    

  		





  
  35
  
    
There are multiple ways to setup your reCAPTCHA API key once you


  		





  
  36
  
    
{obtain}[http://recaptcha.net/whyrecaptcha.html] a pair.


  		





  
  37
  
    

  		





  
  38
  
    
=== Recaptcha.configure


  		





  
  39
  
    

  		





  
  40
  
    
You may use the block style configuration. The following code could be placed


  		





  
  41
  
    
into a +config/initializers/recaptcha.rb+ when used in a Rails project.


  		





  
  42
  
    

  		





  
  43
  
    
  Recaptcha.configure do |config|


  		





  
  44
  
    
    config.public_key  = '6Lc6BAAAAAAAAChqRbQZcn_yyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyy'


  		





  
  45
  
    
    config.private_key = '6Lc6BAAAAAAAAKN3DRm6VA_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx'


  		





  
  46
  
    
    config.proxy = 'http://myproxy.com.au:8080'


  		





  
  47
  
    
  end


  		





  
  48
  
    

  		





  
  49
  
    
This way, you may also set additional options to fit recaptcha into your


  		





  
  50
  
    
deployment environment.


  		





  
  51
  
    

  		





  
  52
  
    
== Recaptcha#with_configuration


  		





  
  53
  
    

  		





  
  54
  
    
If you want to temporarily overwrite the configuration you set with `Recaptcha.configure` (when testing, for example), you can use a `Recaptcha#with_configuration` block:


  		





  
  55
  
    

  		





  
  56
  
    
  Recaptcha.with_configuration(:public_key => '12345') do


  		





  
  57
  
    
    # Do stuff with the overwritten public_key.


  		





  
  58
  
    
  end


  		





  
  59
  
    

  		





  
  60
  
    
=== Heroku & Shell environment


  		





  
  61
  
    

  		





  
  62
  
    
Or, you can keep your keys out of your code base by exporting the following


  		





  
  63
  
    
environment variables. You might do this in the .profile/rc, or equivalent for


  		





  
  64
  
    
the user running your application. This would also be the preffered method


  		





  
  65
  
    
in an Heroku deployment.


  		





  
  66
  
    

  		





  
  67
  
    
  export RECAPTCHA_PUBLIC_KEY  = '6Lc6BAAAAAAAAChqRbQZcn_yyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyy'


  		





  
  68
  
    
  export RECAPTCHA_PRIVATE_KEY = '6Lc6BAAAAAAAAKN3DRm6VA_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx'


  		





  
  69
  
    

  		





  
  70
  
    
=== Per call


  		





  
  71
  
    

  		





  
  72
  
    
You can also pass in your keys as options at runtime, for example:


  		





  
  73
  
    

  		





  
  74
  
    
  recaptcha_tags :public_key => '6Lc6BAAAAAAAAChqRbQZcn_yyyyyyyyyyyyyyyyy'


  		





  
  75
  
    

  		





  
  76
  
    
and later,


  		





  
  77
  
    

  		





  
  78
  
    
  verify_recaptcha :private_key => '6Lc6BAAAAAAAAKN3DRm6VA_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx'


  		





  
  79
  
    

  		





  
  80
  
    
This option might be useful, if the same code base is used for multiple


  		





  
  81
  
    
reCAPTCHA setups.


  		





  
  82
  
    

  		





  
  83
  
    
== To use 'recaptcha'


  		





  
  84
  
    

  		





  
  85
  
    
Add +recaptcha_tags+ to each form you want to protect.


  		





  
  86
  
    

  		





  
  87
  
    
And, add +verify_recaptcha+ logic to each form action that you've protected.


  		





  
  88
  
    

  		





  
  89
  
    
=== +recaptcha_tags+


  		





  
  90
  
    

  		





  
  91
  
    
Some of the options available:


  		





  
  92
  
    

  		





  
  93
  
    
<tt>:ssl</tt>::         Uses secure http for captcha widget (default +false+)


  		





  
  94
  
    
<tt>:noscript</tt>::    Include <noscript> content (default +true+)


  		





  
  95
  
    
<tt>:display</tt>::     Takes a hash containing the +theme+ and +tabindex+ options per the API. (default +nil+)


  		





  
  96
  
    
<tt>:ajax</tt>::        Render the dynamic AJAX captcha per the API. (default +false+)


  		





  
  97
  
    
<tt>:public_key</tt>::  Your public API key, takes precedence over the ENV variable (default +nil+)


  		





  
  98
  
    
<tt>:error</tt>::       Override the error code returned from the reCAPTCHA API (default +nil+)


  		





  
  99
  
    

  		





  
  100
  
    
You can also override the html attributes for the sizes of the generated +textarea+ and +iframe+


  		





  
  101
  
    
elements, if CSS isn't your thing. Inspect the source of +recaptcha_tags+ to see these options.


  		





  
  102
  
    

  		





  
  103
  
    
=== +verify_recaptcha+


  		





  
  104
  
    

  		





  
  105
  
    
This method returns +true+ or +false+ after processing the parameters from the reCAPTCHA widget. Why


  		





  
  106
  
    
isn't this a model validation? Because that violates MVC. You can use it like this, or how ever you


  		





  
  107
  
    
like. Passing in the ActiveRecord object is optional, if you do--and the captcha fails to verify--an


  		





  
  108
  
    
error will be added to the object for you to use.


  		





  
  109
  
    

  		





  
  110
  
    
Some of the options available:


  		





  
  111
  
    

  		





  
  112
  
    
<tt>:model</tt>::       Model to set errors


  		





  
  113
  
    
<tt>:attribute</tt>::   Model attribute to receive errors (default :base)


  		





  
  114
  
    
<tt>:message</tt>::     Custom error message


  		





  
  115
  
    
<tt>:private_key</tt>:: Your private API key, takes precedence over the ENV variable (default +nil+).


  		





  
  116
  
    
<tt>:timeout</tt>::     The number of seconds to wait for reCAPTCHA servers before give up. (default +3+)


  		





  
  117
  
    

  		





  
  118
  
    
  respond_to do |format|


  		





  
  119
  
    
    if verify_recaptcha(:model => @post, :message => "Oh! It's error with reCAPTCHA!") && @post.save


  		





  
  120
  
    
      # ...


  		





  
  121
  
    
    else


  		





  
  122
  
    
      # ...


  		





  
  123
  
    
    end


  		





  
  124
  
    
  end


  		





  
  125
  
    

  		





  
  126
  
    
== I18n support


  		





  
  127
  
    
reCAPTCHA passes two types of error explanation to a linked model. It will use the I18n gem


  		





  
  128
  
    
to translate the default error message if I18n is available. To customize the messages to your locale,


  		





  
  129
  
    
add these keys to your I18n backend:


  		





  
  130
  
    

  		





  
  131
  
    
<tt>recaptcha.errors.verification_failed</tt>:: error message displayed if the captcha words didn't match


  		





  
  132
  
    
<tt>recaptcha.errors.recaptcha_unavailable</tt>:: displayed if a timout error occured while attempting to verify the captcha


  		





  
  133
  
    

  		





  
  134
  
    
Also you can translate API response errors to human friendly by adding translations to the locale (+config/locales/en.yml+):


  		





  
  135
  
    

  		





  
  136
  
    
  en:


  		





  
  137
  
    
    recaptcha:


  		





  
  138
  
    
      errors:


  		





  
  139
  
    
        incorrect-captcha-sol: 'Fail'


  		





  
  140
  
    

  		





  
  141

# Rails plugin initialization.

#   config.gem "ambethia-recaptcha", :lib => "recaptcha/rails", :source => "http://gems.github.com"

require 'recaptcha/configuration'


  		





  
  2
  
    
require 'recaptcha/client_helper'


  		





  
  3
  
    
require 'recaptcha/verify'


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
module Recaptcha


  		





  
  6
  
    
  RECAPTCHA_API_SERVER_URL        = 'http://www.google.com/recaptcha/api'


  		





  
  7
  
    
  RECAPTCHA_API_SECURE_SERVER_URL = 'https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api'


  		





  
  8
  
    
  RECAPTCHA_VERIFY_URL            = 'http://www.google.com/recaptcha/api/verify'


  		





  
  9
  
    

  		





  
  10
  
    
  HANDLE_TIMEOUTS_GRACEFULLY      = true


  		





  
  11
  
    
  SKIP_VERIFY_ENV = ['test', 'cucumber']


  		





  
  12
  
    

  		





  
  13
  
    
  # Gives access to the current Configuration.


  		





  
  14
  
    
  def self.configuration


  		





  
  15
  
    
    @configuration ||= Configuration.new


  		





  
  16
  
    
  end


  		





  
  17
  
    

  		





  
  18
  
    
  # Allows easy setting of multiple configuration options. See Configuration


  		





  
  19
  
    
  # for all available options.


  		





  
  20
  
    
  #--


  		





  
  21
  
    
  # The temp assignment is only used to get a nicer rdoc. Feel free to remove


  		





  
  22
  
    
  # this hack.


  		





  
  23
  
    
  #++


  		





  
  24
  
    
  def self.configure


  		





  
  25
  
    
    config = configuration


  		





  
  26
  
    
    yield(config)


  		





  
  27
  
    
  end


  		





  
  28
  
    

  		





  
  29
  
    
  def self.with_configuration(config)


  		





  
  30
  
    
    original_config = {}


  		





  
  31
  
    

  		





  
  32
  
    
    config.each do |key, value|


  		





  
  33
  
    
      original_config[key] = configuration.send(key)


  		





  
  34
  
    
      configuration.send("#{key}=", value)


  		





  
  35
  
    
    end


  		





  
  36
  
    

  		





  
  37
  
    
    result = yield if block_given?


  		





  
  38
  
    

  		





  
  39
  
    
    original_config.each { |key, value| configuration.send("#{key}=", value) }


  		





  
  40
  
    
    result


  		





  
  41
  
    
  end


  		





  
  42
  
    

  		





  
  43
  
    
  class RecaptchaError < StandardError


  		





  
  44
  
    
  end


  		





  
  45
  
    
end


  		





  
  46
  
    

  		





  
  47
  
    
if defined?(Rails)


  		





  
  48
  
    
  require 'recaptcha/rails'


  		





  
  49
  
    
end


  		












  

    
      b/vendor/plugins/recaptcha/lib/recaptcha/client_helper.rb
    
  






  
  1
  
    
module Recaptcha


  		





  
  2
  
    
  module ClientHelper


  		





  
  3
  
    
    # Your public API can be specified in the +options+ hash or preferably


  		





  
  4
  
    
    # using the Configuration.


  		





  
  5
  
    
    def recaptcha_tags(options = {})


  		





  
  6
  
    
      # Default options


  		





  
  7
  
    
      key   = options[:public_key] ||= Recaptcha.configuration.public_key


  		





  
  8
  
    
      raise RecaptchaError, "No public key specified." unless key


  		





  
  9
  
    
      error = options[:error] ||= ((defined? flash) ? flash[:recaptcha_error] : "")


  		





  
  10
  
    
      uri   = Recaptcha.configuration.api_server_url(options[:ssl])


  		





  
  11
  
    
      lang  = options[:display] && options[:display][:lang] ? options[:display][:lang].to_sym : ""


  		





  
  12
  
    
      html  = ""


  		





  
  13
  
    
      if options[:display]


  		





  
  14
  
    
        html << %{<script type="text/javascript">\n}


  		





  
  15
  
    
        html << %{  var RecaptchaOptions = #{options[:display].to_json};\n}


  		





  
  16
  
    
        html << %{</script>\n}


  		





  
  17
  
    
      end


  		





  
  18
  
    
      if options[:ajax]


  		





  
  19
  
    
        html << <<-EOS


  		





  
  20
  
    
          <div id="dynamic_recaptcha"></div>


  		





  
  21
  
    
          <script type="text/javascript">


  		





  
  22
  
    
            var rc_script_tag = document.createElement('script'),


  		





  
  23
  
    
                rc_init_func = function(){Recaptcha.create("#{key}", document.getElementById("dynamic_recaptcha")#{',RecaptchaOptions' if options[:display]});}


  		





  
  24
  
    
            rc_script_tag.src = "#{uri}/js/recaptcha_ajax.js";


  		





  
  25
  
    
            rc_script_tag.type = 'text/javascript';


  		





  
  26
  
    
            rc_script_tag.onload = function(){rc_init_func.call();};


  		





  
  27
  
    
            rc_script_tag.onreadystatechange = function(){


  		





  
  28
  
    
              if (rc_script_tag.readyState == 'loaded' || rc_script_tag.readyState == 'complete') {rc_init_func.call();}


  		





  
  29
  
    
            };


  		





  
  30
  
    
            (document.getElementsByTagName('head')[0] || document.getElementsByTagName('body')[0]).appendChild(rc_script_tag);


  		





  
  31
  
    
          </script>


  		





  
  32
  
    
        EOS


  		





  
  33
  
    
      else


  		





  
  34
  
    
        html << %{<script type="text/javascript" src="#{uri}/challenge?k=#{key}}


  		





  
  35
  
    
        html << %{#{error ? "&amp;error=#{CGI::escape(error)}" : ""}}


  		





  
  36
  
    
        html << %{#{lang ? "&amp;lang=#{lang}" : ""}"></script>\n}


  		





  
  37
  
    
        unless options[:noscript] == false


  		





  
  38
  
    
          html << %{<noscript>\n  }


  		





  
  39
  
    
          html << %{<iframe src="#{uri}/noscript?k=#{key}" }


  		





  
  40
  
    
          html << %{height="#{options[:iframe_height] ||= 300}" }


  		





  
  41
  
    
          html << %{width="#{options[:iframe_width]   ||= 500}" }


  		





  
  42
  
    
          html << %{style="border:none;"></iframe><br/>\n  }


  		





  
  43
  
    
          html << %{<textarea name="recaptcha_challenge_field" }


  		





  
  44
  
    
          html << %{rows="#{options[:textarea_rows] ||= 3}" }


  		





  
  45
  
    
          html << %{cols="#{options[:textarea_cols] ||= 40}"></textarea>\n  }


  		





  
  46
  
    
          html << %{<input type="hidden" name="recaptcha_response_field" value="manual_challenge"/>}


  		





  
  47
  
    
          html << %{</noscript>\n}


  		





  
  48
  
    
        end


  		





  
  49
  
    
      end


  		





  
  50
  
    
      return (html.respond_to?(:html_safe) && html.html_safe) || html


  		





  
  51
  
    
    end # recaptcha_tags


  		





  
  52
  
    
  end # ClientHelper


  		





  
  53
  
    
end # Recaptcha

  16

require "uri"


  		





  
  2
  
    
module Recaptcha


  		





  
  3
  
    
  module Verify


  		





  
  4
  
    
    # Your private API can be specified in the +options+ hash or preferably


  		





  
  5
  
    
    # using the Configuration.


  		





  
  6
  
    
    def verify_recaptcha(options = {})


  		





  
  7
  
    
      if !options.is_a? Hash


  		





  
  8
  
    
        options = {:model => options}


  		





  
  9
  
    
      end


  		





  
  10
  
    

  		





  
  11
  
    
      env = options[:env] || ENV['RAILS_ENV']


  		





  
  12
  
    
      return true if Recaptcha.configuration.skip_verify_env.include? env


  		





  
  13
  
    
      model = options[:model]


  		





  
  14
  
    
      attribute = options[:attribute] || :base


  		





  
  15
  
    
      private_key = options[:private_key] || Recaptcha.configuration.private_key


  		





  
  16
  
    
      raise RecaptchaError, "No private key specified." unless private_key


  		





  
  17
  
    

  		





  
  18
  
    
      begin


  		





  
  19
  
    
        recaptcha = nil


  		





  
  20
  
    
        if(Recaptcha.configuration.proxy)


  		





  
  21
  
    
          proxy_server = URI.parse(Recaptcha.configuration.proxy)


  		





  
  22
  
    
          http = Net::HTTP::Proxy(proxy_server.host, proxy_server.port, proxy_server.user, proxy_server.password)


  		





  
  23
  
    
        else


  		





  
  24
  
    
          http = Net::HTTP


  		





  
  25
  
    
        end


  		





  
  26
  
    

  		





  
  27
  
    
        Timeout::timeout(options[:timeout] || 3) do


  		





  
  28
  
    
          recaptcha = http.post_form(URI.parse(Recaptcha.configuration.verify_url), {


  		





  
  29
  
    
            "privatekey" => private_key,


  		





  
  30
  
    
            "remoteip"   => request.remote_ip,


  		





  
  31
  
    
            "challenge"  => params[:recaptcha_challenge_field],


  		





  
  32
  
    
            "response"   => params[:recaptcha_response_field]


  		





  
  33
  
    
          })


  		





  
  34
  
    
        end


  		





  
  35
  
    
        answer, error = recaptcha.body.split.map { |s| s.chomp }


  		





  
  36
  
    
        unless answer == 'true'


  		





  
  37
  
    
          flash[:recaptcha_error] = if defined?(I18n)


  		





  
  38
  
    
            I18n.translate("recaptcha.errors.#{error}", {:default => error})


  		





  
  39
  
    
          else


  		





  
  40
  
    
            error


  		





  
  41
  
    
          end


  		





  
  42
  
    

  		





  
  43
  
    
          if model


  		





  
  44
  
    
            message = "Word verification response is incorrect, please try again."


  		





  
  45
  
    
            message = I18n.translate('recaptcha.errors.verification_failed', {:default => message}) if defined?(I18n)


  		





  
  46
  
    
            model.errors.add attribute, options[:message] || message


  		





  
  47
  
    
          end


  		





  
  48
  
    
          return false


  		





  
  49
  
    
        else


  		





  
  50
  
    
          flash.delete(:recaptcha_error)


  		





  
  51
  
    
          return true


  		





  
  52
  
    
        end


  		





  
  53
  
    
      rescue Timeout::Error


  		





  
  54
  
    
        if Recaptcha.configuration.handle_timeouts_gracefully


  		





  
  55
  
    
          flash[:recaptcha_error] = if defined?(I18n)


  		





  
  56
  
    
            I18n.translate('recaptcha.errors.recaptcha_unreachable', {:default => 'Recaptcha unreachable.'})


  		





  
  57
  
    
          else


  		





  
  58
  
    
            'Recaptcha unreachable.'


  		





  
  59
  
    
          end


  		





  
  60
  
    

  		





  
  61
  
    
          if model


  		





  
  62
  
    
            message = "Oops, we failed to validate your word verification response. Please try again."


  		





  
  63
  
    
            message = I18n.translate('recaptcha.errors.recaptcha_unreachable', :default => message) if defined?(I18n)


  		





  
  64
  
    
            model.errors.add attribute, options[:message] || message


  		





  
  65
  
    
          end


  		





  
  66
  
    
          return false


  		





  
  67
  
    
        else


  		





  
  68
  
    
          raise RecaptchaError, "Recaptcha unreachable."


  		





  
  69
  
    
        end


  		





  
  70
  
    
      rescue Exception => e


  		





  
  71
  
    
        raise RecaptchaError, e.message, e.backtrace


  		





  
  72
  
    
      end


  		





  
  73
  
    
    end # verify_recaptcha


  		





  
  74
  
    
  end # Verify


  		





  
  75
  
    
end # Recaptcha

  end

  def test_message_should_use_i18n


  		





  
  88
  
    
    I18n.locale = :de


  		





  
  89
  
    
    verification_failed_translated   = "Sicherheitscode konnte nicht verifiziert werden."


  		





  
  90
  
    
    verification_failed_default      = "Word verification response is incorrect, please try again."


  		





  
  91
  
    
    recaptcha_unreachable_translated = "Netzwerkfehler, bitte versuchen Sie es später erneut."


  		





  
  92
  
    
    recaptcha_unreachable_default    = "Oops, we failed to validate your word verification response. Please try again."


  		





  
  93
  
    

  		





  
  94
  
    
    I18n.expects(:translate).with('recaptcha.errors.bad-news', {:default => 'bad-news'})


  		





  
  95
  
    
    I18n.expects(:translate).with('recaptcha.errors.recaptcha_unreachable', {:default => 'Recaptcha unreachable.'})


  		





  
  96
  
    

  		





  
  97
  
    
    I18n.expects(:translate).with('recaptcha.errors.verification_failed', :default => verification_failed_default).returns(verification_failed_translated)


  		





  
  98
  
    
    I18n.expects(:translate).with('recaptcha.errors.recaptcha_unreachable', :default => recaptcha_unreachable_default).returns(recaptcha_unreachable_translated)


  		





  
  99
  
    

  		





  
  100
  
    
    errors = mock


  		





  
  101
  
    
    errors.expects(:add).with(:base, verification_failed_translated)


  		





  
  102
  
    
    errors.expects(:add).with(:base, recaptcha_unreachable_translated)


  		





  
  103
  
    
    model  = mock; model.stubs(:errors => errors)


  		





  
  104
  
    

  		





  
  105
  
    
    expect_http_post(response_with_body("false\nbad-news"))


  		





  
  106
  
    
    @controller.verify_recaptcha(:model => model)


  		





  
  107
  
    

  		





  
  108
  
    
    expect_http_post(Timeout::Error, :exception => true)


  		





  
  109
  
    
    @controller.verify_recaptcha(:model => model)


  		





  
  110
  
    

  		





  
  111
  
    
  end

  def expect_http_post(response, options = {})


  		





  
  141
  
    
    unless options[:exception]


  		





  
  142
  
    
      Net::HTTP.expects(:post_form).with(@expected_uri, @expected_post_data).returns(response)


  		





  
  143
  
    
    else


  		





  
  144
  
    
      Net::HTTP.expects(:post_form).raises response


  		





  
  145
  
    
    end


  		





  
  146
  
    
  end

  end


  		





  
  151

      b/vendor/plugins/redmine_recaptcha/Gemfile
    
  






  
  1
  
    
gem "recaptcha", :require => "recaptcha/rails"


  		












  

    
      b/vendor/plugins/redmine_recaptcha/README
    
  






  
  1
  
    
redmine_recaptcha


  		





  
  2
  
    

  		





  
  3
  
    
srstclair@gmail.com


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
Simple Redmine/ChiliProject plugin to add a reCAPTCHA to user self registration.


  		





  
  6
  
    

  		





  
  7
  
    
Relies on ambethia's recaptcha for rails plugin (http://github.com/ambethia/recaptcha/)


  		





  
  8
  
    

  		





  
  9
  
    
To install:


  		





  
  10
  
    

  		





  
  11
  
    
make sure you have git installed!


  		





  
  12
  
    

  		





  
  13
  
    
cd to your Redmine/ChiliProject directory


  		





  
  14
  
    

  		





  
  15
  
    

  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
install the plugin (for Redmine users):


  		





  
  18
  
    
sudo ruby script/plugin install git://github.com/ambethia/recaptcha.git


  		





  
  19
  
    
sudo ruby script/plugin install git://github.com/srstclair/redmine_recaptcha.git 


  		





  
  20
  
    

  		





  
  21
  
    
OR install the plugin (for Chiliproject users):


  		





  
  22
  
    
sudo ruby script/plugin install git://github.com/srstclair/redmine_recaptcha.git 


  		





  
  23
  
    
sudo bundle install


  		





  
  24
  
    

  		





  
  25
  
    

  		





  
  26
  
    

  		





  
  27
  
    
restart Redmine/ChiliProject


  		





  
  28
  
    

  		





  
  29
  
    
sign in as an administrator


  		





  
  30
  
    

  		





  
  31
  
    
go to Administration/Plugins/reCAPTCHA/Configure


  		





  
  32
  
    

  		





  
  33
  
    
sign up for a recaptcha key at http://www.google.com/recaptcha (if you haven't already)


  		





  
  34
  
    

  		





  
  35
  
    
enter your public and private recaptcha keys


  		





  
  36
  
    

  		





  
  37
  
    
go to self registration page to see captcha!


  		












  

    
      b/vendor/plugins/redmine_recaptcha/app/views/account/register.rhtml

Redmine::Plugin.register :redmine_recaptcha do


  		





  
  20
  
    
  name 'reCAPTCHA for user self registration'


  		





  
  21
  
    
  author 'Shane StClair'


  		





  
  22
  
    
  description 'Adds a recaptcha to the user self registration screen to combat spam'


  		





  
  23
  
    
  version '0.1.0'


  		





  
  24
  
    
  url 'http://github.com/srstclair/redmine_recaptcha'


  		





  
  25
  
    
  #requires_redmine :version_or_higher => '0.9.0'


  		





  
  26
  
    
  settings :default => {


  		





  
  27
  
    
     'recaptcha_private_key' => '',


  		





  
  28
  
    
     'recaptcha_public_key' => ''


  		





  
  29
  
    
  }, :partial => 'settings/redmine_recaptcha'


  		





  
  30
  
    

  		





  
  31
  
    
end

      b/vendor/plugins/redmine_recaptcha/lib/account_controller_patch.rb
    
  






  
  1
  
    
module AccountControllerPatch


  		





  
  2
  
    
  def self.included(base)


  		





  
  3
  
    
    base.send(:include, InstanceMethods)


  		





  
  4
  
    

  		





  
  5
  
    
    base.class_eval do


  		





  
  6
  
    
      alias_method_chain :register, :recaptcha_verification


  		





  
  7
  
    
    end


  		





  
  8
  
    
  end


  		





  
  9
  
    
  


  		





  
  10
  
    
  module InstanceMethods


  		





  
  11
  
    
    def register_with_recaptcha_verification


  		





  
  12
  
    
      redirect_to(home_url) && return unless Setting.self_registration? || session[:auth_source_registration]


  		





  
  13
  
    

  		





  
  14
  
    
      if request.get?


  		





  
  15
  
    
        session[:auth_source_registration] = nil


  		





  
  16
  
    
        @user = User.new(:language => Setting.default_language)


  		





  
  17
  
    
      else


  		





  
  18
  
    
        @user = User.new(params[:user])


  		





  
  19
  
    
        @user.admin = false


  		





  
  20
  
    
        @user.register


  		





  
  21
  
    
        if session[:auth_source_registration]


  		





  
  22
  
    
          @user.activate


  		





  
  23
  
    
          @user.login = session[:auth_source_registration][:login]


  		





  
  24
  
    
          @user.auth_source_id = session[:auth_source_registration][:auth_source_id]


  		





  
  25
  
    
          if @user.save


  		





  
  26
  
    
            session[:auth_source_registration] = nil


  		





  
  27
  
    
            self.logged_user = @user


  		





  
  28
  
    
            flash[:notice] = l(:notice_account_activated)


  		





  
  29
  
    
            redirect_to :controller => 'my', :action => 'account'


  		





  
  30
  
    
          end


  		





  
  31
  
    
        else


  		





  
  32
  
    
          @user.login = params[:user][:login]


  		





  
  33
  
    
          @user.password, @user.password_confirmation = params[:password], params[:password_confirmation]


  		





  
  34
  
    
          if verify_recaptcha( :private_key => Setting.plugin_redmine_recaptcha['recaptcha_private_key'], :model => @user, :message => "There was an error with the recaptcha code below. Please re-enter the code and click submit." )


  		





  
  35
  
    
            case Setting.self_registration


  		





  
  36
  
    
            when '1'


  		





  
  37
  
    
              register_by_email_activation(@user)


  		





  
  38
  
    
            when '3'


  		





  
  39
  
    
              register_automatically(@user)


  		





  
  40
  
    
            else


  		





  
  41
  
    
              register_manually_by_administrator(@user)


  		





  
  42
  
    
            end


  		





  
  43
  
    
          end


  		





  
  44
  
    
        end


  		





  
  45
  
    

  		





  
  46
  
    
        #the old method is accessible here:


  		





  
  47
  
    
        #register_without_recaptcha_verification


  		





  
  48
  
    
      end


  		





  
  49
  
    
    end


  		





  
  50
  
    
  end


  		





  
  51
  
    
end


  		












  

    
      b/vendor/plugins/redmine_recaptcha/lib/client_helper_patch.rb
    
  






  
  1
  
    
module ClientHelperPatch


  		





  
  2
  
    
  def self.included(base)


  		





  
  3
  
    
    base.send(:include, InstanceMethods)


  		





  
  4
  
    
    base.class_eval do


  		





  
  5
  
    
      alias_method_chain :recaptcha_tags, :flash_remove


  		





  
  6
  
    
    end


  		





  
  7
  
    
  end


  		





  
  8
  
    

  		





  
  9
  
    
  module InstanceMethods


  		





  
  10
  
    
    def recaptcha_tags_with_flash_remove(options={})


  		





  
  11
  
    
      html = recaptcha_tags_without_flash_remove( options )


  		





  
  12
  
    
      flash.delete( :recaptcha_error )


  		





  
  13
  
    
      return html


  		





  
  14
  
    
    end


  		





  
  15
  
    
  end


  		





  
  16
  
    
end

class RoleShiftsController < ApplicationController


  		





  
  2
  
    
    model_object RoleShift


  		





  
  3
  
    
    before_filter :find_project, :only => :new


  		





  
  4
  
    
    before_filter :find_model_object, :except => :new


  		





  
  5
  
    
    before_filter :find_project_from_association, :except => :new


  		





  
  6
  
    
    before_filter :authorize


  		





  
  7
  
    

  		





  
  8
  
    
    def new


  		





  
  9
  
    
        if request.post? && params[:role_shift]


  		





  
  10
  
    
            @role_shift = RoleShift.new(params[:role_shift].merge(:project => @project))


  		





  
  11
  
    
            @role_shift.save


  		





  
  12
  
    
        end


  		





  
  13
  
    
        respond_to do |format|


  		





  
  14
  
    
            format.html { redirect_to(:controller => 'projects', :action => 'settings', :tab => 'roles', :id => @project) }


  		





  
  15
  
    
            format.js do


  		





  
  16
  
    
                render(:update) do |page|


  		





  
  17
  
    
                    page.replace_html('tab-content-roles', :partial => 'projects/settings/role_shifts')


  		





  
  18
  
    
                    page << 'hideOnLoad()'


  		





  
  19
  
    
                    page.visual_effect(:highlight, "role-shift-#{@role_shift.id}")


  		





  
  20
  
    
                end


  		





  
  21
  
    
            end


  		





  
  22
  
    
        end


  		





  
  23
  
    
    end


  		





  
  24
  
    

  		





  
  25
  
    
    def edit


  		





  
  26
  
    
        if request.post? && params[:role_shift]


  		





  
  27
  
    
            @role_shift.update_attributes(params[:role_shift])


  		





  
  28
  
    
        end


  		





  
  29
  
    
        respond_to do |format|


  		





  
  30
  
    
            format.html { redirect_to(:controller => 'projects', :action => 'settings', :tab => 'roles', :id => @project) }


  		





  
  31
  
    
            format.js do


  		





  
  32
  
    
                render(:update) do |page|


  		





  
  33
  
    
                    page.replace_html('tab-content-roles', :partial => 'projects/settings/role_shifts')


  		





  
  34
  
    
                    page << 'hideOnLoad()'


  		





  
  35
  
    
                    page.visual_effect(:highlight, "role-shift-#{@role_shift.id}")


  		





  
  36
  
    
                end


  		





  
  37
  
    
            end


  		





  
  38
  
    
        end


  		





  
  39
  
    
    end


  		





  
  40
  
    

  		





  
  41
  
    
    def destroy


  		





  
  42
  
    
        if request.post?


  		





  
  43
  
    
            @role_shift.destroy


  		





  
  44
  
    
        end


  		





  
  45

            format.html { redirect_to(:controller => 'projects', :action => 'settings', :tab => 'roles', :id => @project) }

      b/vendor/plugins/role_shift/app/models/role_shift.rb

class RoleShift < ActiveRecord::Base


  		





  
  2
  
    
    belongs_to :project


  		





  
  3
  
    
    belongs_to :role, :foreign_key => 'role_id'


  		





  
  4
  
    
    belongs_to :shift, :class_name => 'Role', :foreign_key => 'shift_id'


  		





  
  5
  
    

  		





  
  6
  
    
    validates_presence_of :project, :role, :shift


  		





  
  7
  
    
    validates_uniqueness_of :role_id, :scope => :project_id


  		





  
  8
  
    

  		





  
  9
  
    
    validate :validate_roles


  		





  
  10
  
    

  		





  
  11
  
    
    def to_role


  		





  
  12
  
    
        replacement = role.clone


  		





  
  13
  
    
        replacement.id = role.id


  		





  
  14
  
    
        replacement.name = "#{role.name} (#{shift.name})"


  		





  
  15
  
    
        if role.builtin == Role::BUILTIN_NON_MEMBER


  		





  
  16
  
    
            replacement.permissions = shift.permissions - Redmine::AccessControl.members_only_permissions


  		





  
  17
  
    
        elsif role.builtin == Role::BUILTIN_ANONYMOUS


  		





  
  18
  
    
            replacement.permissions = shift.permissions - Redmine::AccessControl.loggedin_only_permissions


  		





  
  19
  
    
        else


  		





  
  20
  
    
            replacement.permissions = shift.permissions


  		





  
  21
  
    
        end


  		





  
  22
  
    
        replacement.issues_visibility = shift.issues_visibility if replacement.has_attribute?(:issues_visibility)


  		





  
  23
  
    
        replacement


  		





  
  24
  
    
    end


  		





  
  25
  
    

  		





  
  26
  
    
private


  		





  
  27
  
    

  		





  
  28
  
    
    def validate_roles


  		





  
  29
  
    
        errors.add(:shift_id, :cant_be_the_same_as_role) if role_id == shift_id


  		





  
  30
  
    
    end


  		





  
  31
  
    

  		





  
  32
  
    
end

class CreateRoleShifts < ActiveRecord::Migration


  		





  
  2

  4

  5
  
    
            t.column :project_id, :integer, :null => false


  		





  
  6
  
    
            t.column :role_id,    :integer, :null => false


  		





  
  7
  
    
            t.column :shift_id,   :integer, :null => false


  		





  
  8
  
    
        end


  		





  
  9
  
    
        add_index :role_shifts, :project_id, :name => :role_shifts_project_ids


  		





  
  10
  
    
    end


  		





  
  11

    end

module ShiftUserPatch

  5
  
    
    def self.included(base)


  		





  
  6
  
    
        base.extend(ClassMethods)


  		





  
  7
  
    
        base.send(:include, InstanceMethods)


  		





  
  8
  
    
        base.class_eval do


  		





  
  9
  
    
            unloadable


  		





  
  10
  
    
            alias_method_chain :roles_for_project, :shift


  		





  
  11
  
    
        end


  		





  
  12
  
    
    end


  		





  
  13
  
    

  		





  
  14
  
    
    module ClassMethods


  		





  
  15
  
    
    end


  		





  
  16
  
    

  		





  
  17
  
    
    module InstanceMethods


  		





  
  18
  
    

  		





  
  19
  
    
        def roles_for_project_with_shift(project)


  		





  
  20
  
    
            roles = roles_for_project_without_shift(project)


  		





  
  21
  
    

  		





  
  22
  
    
            if project.module_enabled?(:role_shifts)


  		





  
  23
  
    
                shifts = RoleShift.find(:all, :conditions => { :project_id => project.id }).inject({}) do |hash, shift|


  		





  
  24
  
    
                    hash[shift.role.id] = shift


  		





  
  25
  
    
                    hash


  		





  
  26
  
    
                end


  		





  
  27
  
    

  		





  
  28
  
    
                roles.collect do |role|


  		





  
  29
  
    
                    shifts[role.id] ? shifts[role.id].to_role : role


  		





  
  30
  
    
                end


  		





  
  31
  
    
            else


  		





  
  32
  
    
                roles


  		





  
  33
  
    
            end


  		





  
  34
  
    
        end


  		





  
  35
  
    

  		





  
  36
  
    
    end


  		





  
  37
  
    

  		





  
  38
  
    
end

class SidebarController < ApplicationController


  		





  
  2
  
    
    before_filter :find_project


  		





  
  3
  
    
    before_filter :find_sidebar_content


  		





  
  4
  
    
    before_filter :authorize


  		





  
  5
  
    

  		





  
  6
  
    
    def edit


  		





  
  7
  
    
        if params[:sidebar][:content_type].present?


  		





  
  8
  
    
            if @sidebar


  		





  
  9
  
    
                if @sidebar.update_attributes(params[:sidebar])


  		





  
  10
  
    
                    flash[:notice] = l(:notice_successful_update)


  		





  
  11
  
    
                else


  		





  
  12
  
    
                    flash[:error] = @sidebar.errors.full_messages.join(', ')


  		





  
  13
  
    
                end


  		





  
  14
  
    
            else


  		





  
  15
  
    
                attrs = params[:sidebar].dup


  		





  
  16
  
    
                @sidebar = SidebarContent.new(attrs.merge(:project => @project))


  		





  
  17
  
    
                if @sidebar.save


  		





  
  18
  
    
                    flash[:notice] = l(:notice_successful_create)


  		





  
  19
  
    
                else


  		





  
  20
  
    
                    flash[:error] = @sidebar.errors.full_messages.join(', ')


  		





  
  21
  
    
                end


  		





  
  22
  
    
            end


  		





  
  23
  
    
        else


  		





  
  24
  
    
            if @sidebar && @sidebar.destroy


  		





  
  25
  
    
                flash[:notice] = l(:notice_successful_delete)


  		





  
  26
  
    
            end


  		





  
  27
  
    
        end


  		





  
  28
  
    
        redirect_to(:controller => 'projects', :action => 'settings', :tab => 'sidebar', :sidebar => params[:sidebar]) # FIXME: use remote form + update


  		





  
  29
  
    
    end


  		





  
  30
  
    

  		





  
  31
  
    
    def preview


  		





  
  32
  
    
        if params[:sidebar]


  		





  
  33
  
    
            @previewed = @sidebar


  		





  
  34
  
    
            case params[:sidebar][:content_type]


  		





  
  35
  
    
            when 'text'


  		





  
  36
  
    
                @text = params[:sidebar][:content] ? params[:sidebar][:content][:text] : nil


  		





  
  37
  
    
                render(:partial => 'common/preview')


  		





  
  38
  
    
            when 'wiki'


  		





  
  39
  
    
                page = @project && @project.wiki && params[:sidebar][:content] ?


  		





  
  40
  
    
                       @project.wiki.find_page(params[:sidebar][:content][:wiki]) : nil


  		





  
  41
  
    
                @text = ''


  		





  
  42
  
    
                if page


  		





  
  43
  
    
                    @text = page.text


  		





  
  44
  
    
                end


  		





  
  45
  
    
                render(:partial => 'common/preview')


  		





  
  46
  
    
            when 'html'


  		





  
  47
  
    
                html = '<fieldset class="preview">'


  		





  
  48
  
    
                html << '<legend>' + l(:label_preview) + '</legend>'


  		





  
  49
  
    
                if params[:sidebar][:content]


  		





  
  50
  
    
                    html << params[:sidebar][:content][:html]


  		





  
  51
  
    
                end


  		





  
  52
  
    
                html << '</fieldset>'


  		





  
  53
  
    
                render(:text => html)


  		





  
  54
  
    
            else


  		





  
  55
  
    
                render_403


  		





  
  56
  
    
            end


  		





  
  57
  
    
        end


  		





  
  58
  
    
    end
